\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 1910 you lived there 'til.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What - in service? Well there's - I used to do very small jobs - er - in several - several in Paddington near my home until I went straight into service at - er the age of fifteen, sixteen and I was a kitchen maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you give me from the eldest down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - what their names? Well the old - er - eleven of us altogether - yes, yes. The first one was a boy - Archibald Henry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And when was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2522858\charrsid10431346 her born}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh I can't remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was he a lot older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He's the eldest one - I'm - I'm seventh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And then we were all born around eighteen months in between - yes - on - on average.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So there was Archibald the oldest and then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Then come Herbert - then Ethel that went down to Leaster, and then Emily that's at Reading - Emily - then him that was a policeman.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Cedric?
