\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Lawrence - Edith, me - Frank - William - er - Ernest and Eva, the youngest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The youngest one was a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And there was roughly eighteen months between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - roughly - yes - some were a year and eight months, year and five months but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No I wouldn't know that. I know he was seventy when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what year did he die in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Now that I could know. What year ... - er - he died after - I think my mother died in 1925 I think. Wait a moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You say your father died in 1927 and he was seventy so he would have been born in 1857?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, I guess - yes - I gather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - Bedfordshire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you happen to know the name of the town or village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - as far as I know - Ampthill. Yes. Or was it my mothers - er - well I can't think exactly - but I know my mothers home was - er - Bedfordshire and I suppose father come from that way too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was your father's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - coachman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did he have any other job before or after he became a coachman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, as far as I can remember he was coachman all - as far as I can remember anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 All his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did he have any casual or part time jobs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He was just a coachman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right. For private service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well if she was two years - she died two years after - er - before father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In 1925?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Right. It would be - and I'm twenty - and mother - father was '27 wasn't he - he died after it. 1925.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That was when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when she was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Where she was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. When.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No I couldn't tell you - she was - it was 1925 when she died - and she was sixty-eight. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So she was born in 1857?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your mother came from Bedfordshire too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Had she any jobs before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - I presume she was in service
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She was in service too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she work after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not at all - no part time jobs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
I would like to ask you about life at home when you were a child - from the time up until you left school. How many rooms were there in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Four. Small rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What were they - kitchen and ......?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
That was a kitchen and two small bedrooms and a little living room. Living room about half the size of this. And it housed all us lot - 'course the older ones .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what's this room - about 10 x 10 I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I know the carpets 10 x 12 that's all I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I should think it's about 11 x 13 perhaps. And did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh heavens no. You've got to laugh at these things haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did it all herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, everything. It was put across the mews on a line from one wall to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - yes mother used to make - er - um - bits and pieces of our clothes and - er - father used to do - used to mend all our boots with a - with a hobbing-foot, as we used to call it. Do you know what a hobbing-foot is? It's - er a round
 piece of wood with - er - you know how the boot menders now put it on a hob - well there's three sizes - and he mend - mended all our shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were the clothes that you had new or secondhand, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, no - but the majority - we
 - er - mother was very grateful if anyone gave her odd things and as we grew up we had to - as we grew out of 'em - the next - er - sister had to - wore them. Like my sister grew out of them I used to have them. So that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when she bought clothes, where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes she - there used to be a shop in Howe Road that used to be - er - um - a cheap shop as well as a pawnbrokers - you could get very reasonable things there er - probably worn things that she thought that w
ould suit one of us - if she'd got the money for it then she'd get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't remember the name of the shop do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - wait a minute now - ooh my memory's gone - I do know it but I - just can't remember the name of the shop now. It's in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Howe Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} I know. If my sister-in-law was here she'd tell you in a minute - she'd got a brain like .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father help you mother with any of the jobs in the house? Like cleaning or cooking or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - he'd do the windows sometimes 
- oh no the washing up had to be done by the children - when they come home from school - yes - we all had our jobs to do. I had to get the young baby to sleep lunch time or peel - peel the potatoes and - er - another one had to wash up - do the washing u
p.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 My mother done all the cooking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your father didn't do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no. Mother did all the cooking on a funny little old stove that stood right out into - into the kitchen - it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7152263\charrsid10431346 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  coal - and we'd have a
 coal bunker at the side - and everything was done on this funny little old stove - big old pots for what - for gravy and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about things like doing the fires? Did your mother or father do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well - father used to be 
out - you see - when he was a coachman he used to have to go to the house and do a certain amount of jobs - sort of clean the windows there and the yards and all sorts of odd jobs so he didn't - he wasn't home a great deal. And then he had to keep his hor
se and his coach clean and er - they used to keep them in the mews, underneath us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Underneath where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about things like decorating and repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh my father - father - or one of the older boys probably, if he was home, you see, they'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember, did your father ever help to dress or undress or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I can't remember that. I don't think so, but I think that - we children relied on on another. See,
 what mum - we used to be told to get undressed and get to bed and if we didn't do we - er - had a clout sort of thing, and say well that's the last time I tell you and - er - we didn't ask for any more, so that we used to get ourselves undressed. But I t
hink us older girls as we were older used to put the younger ones to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember your father ever reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes he might have told us a little - a little story sort of thing, but - er - I can't remember him ever reading to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And would he tell you stories at bed time or just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well just as we were sort of there - sort of after - once we got indoors and stayed indoors, you see, we could play in the mews, never
 got anywhere, just stayed in the mews amongst the horses. Used to have real fun there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you're not frightened of horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no. Always used to play hide and seek and there was quite a few children in the mews, you see, there's a mews you 
know with only one - you can't go through, not entrance the other side, there's a cul-de-sac at the bottom, you see, and there was all carriages dotted about and all cobble stones and we didn't mind one little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father ever take you out without your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I don't remember him - but mother used to take us out sometimes, the whole, you know, crew of us and the younger ones of course not probably one of the older sisters that was probably already in service - had her half day off a
nd we used to - er - go to Wormwood Scrubs, as a great treat, on the open buses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And do you remember your father ever looking after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Mother never went out - she hadn't got time. The only time - only time mother went
 out was about ten o'clock on a Saturday night, when all the shops - people had finished their shops to go up there to get something reasonable - er }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7152263\charrsid10431346 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  and tradesmen then used to sell their - er - goods quite reasonable. Yes. And she'd get - er - we never h
ad lamb - it was always a shoulder of mutton and - er everything was most reasonable, of course, naturally on Saturday night. My father was of course - er - he had twenty-six shillings a week - and - er - six of that used to go for rent so that we was alw
ays - mother was only to pleased to go and get what we could. And she went - yes - yes - after we was all bathed - we had a bath in front of the fire in a zinc bath and each - each one went in with a drop more hot water in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you tell me what they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - we used to - in the morning of course we had to go out and clean doorsteps and then probably do the shopping before school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your doorsteps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - other peoples doorsteps. For about sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you, for instance, clean all the others in the mews?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh not in the mews - Alexander Street was a street where - er - better class people - probably a person 
kept a house and only just sort of got one maid and then as the doorsteps were all those horrible hearth stones and two or three steps down to the gate - hearthstone - and we had to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What time in the morning would you be doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well
 I suppose we would - have to do it before school time - never bothered with what time we had - had to be up before eight o'clock because we had to be at school at nine. In the mornings we didn't do - I didn't - I'm talking about myself - my sister used t
o do the same - and the mornings we didn't do doorsteps, we used to have to go out do shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about when you came home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Lunch time - no - we all had our jobs lunchtime - one of us had to do potatoes or washing up or and get the
 young girl - baby to bed-or vice versa - one had to do - there was always a certain amount before we went back to school again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, evening - no, there wasn't a great deal to do - we had our tea and we went out 
and played in the mews until bed time and - er - or if - a new jobs to be done. Saturdays of course we had to do a certain amount of cleaning - either wash the stairs down or - or do some of the floors or do - do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You were kept very busy weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long did you carry on doing those tasks - right up until you went into service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Right up until I went into - went into my first job at about fourteen when I left school and I went into a place - er - I slept
 there - er - quite near home - with two elderly ladies - and all my sister went there previous. And then I think I was there for about eighteen months - er - I to - up to two years, and then - er - my fathers people were Jewish and they were friends with
 
some people in Westbourne Terrace and every so often his lady used to ask her friends if - er - if Talbot - that's Talbot - my father - used to have any more daughters available for service. So as we come along eighteen months at a time of course we went 
to service. And I went into service when I was about fifteen and a half I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you were working for them you were staying there full time were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, full time, but I used to come home of an evening time but I had to be in at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you do anything when you came home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, not then. Well I would say if mother wanted anything done of course we used to - er - but of course all the work - the children were in bed by nine o'clock see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you 
were at school. You told me earlier that the older children helped the younger with things they found difficult - so they would help them with dressing and eating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember any other ways particularly in which they looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well we used to take them out - when they were too young in a very funny old mail cart. A - a wooden one with - er - seat back to back - just wood - no springs. And one was tied in the front of us and one in the back and you got two big }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2522858\charrsid10431346 wheels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  and two tiny wheels and it used to rattle like blazes and we used to chase }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2522858\charrsid10431346 over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  these cobblestones - it was real fun to. Oh yes, we always had to take the children out, certain times - after school mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did the younger children help the older children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The younger ones - oh no, well they wouldn't be - old enough to do any help. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, we had to be in - in bed round about eight. Yes, right up to the time we went out to service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You were in bed by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 7}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past seven{\*\xmlclose} or eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 7}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}Half past seven{\*\xmlclose} or eight - yes. Very seldom went to sleep of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, we had to get to bed ourselves. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about when you were an older child - did you help the little ones to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well - mother used to put those to bed before then, you see, they used to go to bed earlier, you see, naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 At what age do you remember putting yourself to bed, first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh I say - I can't remember that - I mean to say - I suppose - we always - always done it - from when we were old enough to do it. Six or seven, probably before then. One can't remember quite when your at four or five can you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. And we had - I'll tell you - we had a very small bedroom with no window and a door and there was two small beds - single beds - where two - us two girls was in one bed and two boys - younger boys
 than we were - in the other one and just a chair between and just a box at the bottom - that's the size of the bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you sleep with your elder sister or your younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 My elder sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The one immediately older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you say there was no window - was there any sort of ventilation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, through - the bedroom faced the kitchen - and there was a left window and mother used to open that of a night time. From the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And where did the rest of the family sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well that's four of us - um - mother and father in the bigger bedroom with just a skylight and there was another single bed in there with two others in. Yes. And then the older ones - two of the older boys or one of
 the older boys that went out - er - quite young - let me think now - fourteen or fifteen - he slept in this job in Owens in - in Westbourne grove he worked - then my elder brother - two older sisters were already in service so they didn't sleep at home, 
y
ou see, they got their - yes - and the two - the eldest brother of all was - er - well he had chest trouble and during the war - um - he went to the country and he stayed there - he never came back - we used to see him often but - the next brother used to
 work at Whiteleys - he would be there for about forty-fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was Whiteleys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Whiteleys was sort of a shop like Selfridges - and he was in the stockroom - to do parcels and all that sort of thing. And he used to sleep at home - but he had a bed - a put-you-up bed in the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the front room downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. No not downstairs - it was all on the one level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Because you were above the stables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I think you said earlier that you bathed in front of the fire in a zinc bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. We had - er - one - er - every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would that be in front of the kitchen fire or the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh the kitchen fire - yes. Every Saturday - and we used to ask - we used to bath the younger on
es while mother was out shopping, that's what we would have done - and there was always kettle on the stove - just coal - no gas - we never had no gas then - it was lamps then and - um - we used to put a drop more water in for the next one - kept filling 
it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I expect the last one had a nice one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could almost cut it with a knife I expect.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when you had clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh every Saturday - yes. Yes - every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have them in between - in the week at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - oh well - probably if we dirtied them that much - er - I expect we did do but - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you were expected to keep them clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - we didn't wash them of course - mother was always washing but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7152263\charrsid10431346 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  er - I presume we had clean clothes in the week but that sort of thing doesn't sort of well - keep in your mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But it was Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh Saturday night we always had clean clothes. Of course naturally we had - I know we used to wear over - em - sort of pinafores - and often you used to have a clean pinafore to go to school with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember where the family had their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the kitchen - at a big table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any occasions when they used another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - er - we used to have - er - of a Sun
day when the boys were home - like from - er - like my elder brother and that and they - and some of the elder boys used to have them in the front room. So there was about five, six seven of us in the kitchen and the rest in the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And would your mother and father be in the front room with the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - we - we were in the kitchen with mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And your father - would he be .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, oh yes he had to see - er - see that we behaved ourselves. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And your mother cooked on a stove - could you describe that to me again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. It's - er - well I think it's - er - well not exactly a portable stove but it used to stand out in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How high was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - high - about - er - about that height.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 About three feet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. And it stood out in the room - it had a chimney that - er - iron or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2522858\charrsid10431346 
galvanized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , you know, used to come - was in the room - used - through the ceiling sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And about how square was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh about - that size - that size.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 About two foot square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. Just got two - er - just got one hole on the top for - filling the coal in and another one just further along where you took off if you were wanting to boil something - and a very small oven about that si
ze - I don't know how she managed - it's wonderful how she did manage - I don't really know how she did manage. She used to have to make a - er - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1058965\charrsid10431346 whopping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  big apple pie - this was Sundays - always had apple pie every Sunday and - um - shoulder of mutton,
 not lamb, probably didn't buy anything else - no beef - we had to have it - and - er - then used to sit - when we go in from - we had to go to Sunday school twice on a Sunday and Church at night, if we didn't play truant.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when breakfast was eaten, what time? Did everybody have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - well father used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1058965\charrsid10431346 have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  to go out, I suppose to do something, see to his horses, you see, then come in and have his breakfast later on. But that was probably after we'd gone to s
chool. 'Cos we had to be at school by nine so that mean leaving home about quarter to nine, you see, then we had to get the doorsteps done by that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you do doorsteps before you had breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Before - yes - before breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you'd have breakfast about what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Half past eight - yes. Piece of bread and dripping and a cup of weak tea and that was your lot. Those days it was good dripping - we used to get some from the house as I told you and it used to be lovely dripping and - er - we never wanted anything else.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 All the people who would eat breakfast together would be the schoolchildren?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. That's right. Well the older ones were already gone - probably they'd have had theirs. Well there was only about - there was only
 the one boy, the older boy, the other worked in, you see - there was up to my sister - er - there was baby - there was one, two, three, four - no - wait a minute - er - Bill and Frank - five, six of us usually - about six - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you had a cup of weak tea and a slice of bread and dripping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever have anything different on Sundays for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes we used to have - for breakfast? Er - no - it was always - er - you know, we had breakfast, we had any dinner on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't have any dinner on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No. But of course father wasn't paid until after dinner time so we used to have - er - sort of fish - dried haddock or something for tea. Or for dinner late you see, once he'd finished - er - work - of 
course, being Jewish people they never went out on a Saturday - from Saturday to a Sunday morning, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What about when you were at school - you'd have that for breakfast then you'd come home for lunch - do you remember what sort of thing you had for lunch on a school day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes, we - we always used to have a good lunch - mum always made a really good meal - er - we had a meat pudding - it was always a huge big thing with er - three or four inches of - er - suet - real good suet - you know, 
beef suet as it was then, that was a meal in itself and vegetables and - er - of course we had plenty of vegetables we - we could get potatoes then about four pounds for tuppence - six pounds for tuppence I believe, that sort of thing, so we always had a 
good meal and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have a pudding afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
A sweet of some kind - either milk pudding or - er - pastry with apples, something like that - get thick pastry with very few apples that sort of - anything to fill you up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have special food on Saturday - you said your people were Jewish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well we didn't have much - we used to have - a bit of bread and butter and that probably some jam for tea - with the fish, you see, that made a meal - but we could always go in during the m
orning and have some - er - mum used to fill the teapot up with water and as it was emptied so more water went in so we used to have - we used to love cold tea and there used to be a mug in the cupboard ready for whoever wanted it - we very seldom had wat
e
r - it was always just this tea - why, because it looked like water, but - but then we had two or three pieces of bread and dripping or we used to be very fond of demerara sugar then - it used to be called yellow crystals - it was very good sugar - and we
 used to have a piece of that with margarine with thick piece and that would - well satisfy us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And Sunday you always had a shoulder of mutton and an apple pie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, yes, that was the usual. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about tea on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Tea - no 
- mother used to make a few cakes and all that sort of thing, we used to have plenty of bread and jam, bread and dripping again, and that, and if there were any cakes there we had a few. But we used to - were very glad of - when my - er - father was worki
n
g in the big house there, the cook was very good to us, and every Saturday my sister and - or one of us would have to go and collect all the pieces of - er - bread and she was very good in putting pieces of cake in - as they cut off the cake, you know, an
d all sorts of things - little tit bits that come in handy for the rest of all the week you see - mother used to make a bread pudding with that and we'd have bread pudding sometimes, you see, she made a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 whopping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  thing about that size. As much would go in the oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you drink much milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh no. We never had much milk - not as regards to drink - no. No - we never we had cups of tea and - it was very weak at that of course, mother had and naturally father had proper tea but we didn't like such strong tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never see her do it - whether she did - she might have done, but I never see her. Can't remember her doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er no - we were very good when we were in servi
ce - er - we used to earn a few shillings - and then we used to - er - collect and bring mother little bit what we could, you see, and in those days, you see, we used - er - be allowed a certain amount of - er - cleaning materials, such as - er - used to 
h
ave so many boxes of matches for lighting a fire - er - it wasn't Vim in those days but a piece of - a square piece of what they called sapoleo and - er - used to be tins of enamaline for pol - blackleading fires - and we had a tin - every so often we wer
e given one of those. What we didn't use, naturally, I used to take home to mother, 'cos it was our - it was given to us to work with - we never give it back again. And pieces of soap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you get food as well, things like ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, when I was i
n - a kitchen maid - the cook - she'd say to me oh your mother'll be glad of that wouldn't she. So I'd say oh yes please - and she'd give us dripping and probably pieces that - I never minded - so daren't mind what people gave us 'cos it all came in very 
handy you see - I don't know how mother would have lived otherwise.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you don't remember her making jam or bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think - I don't think she had - she hadn't got the facilities to do it with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Or making wine or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh heavens, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she make any medicines at all for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well she used to - we used to have medicine every Saturday. Er - one used to be liquorice powder and another one was senna tea - which we had more - if we could get near the sink we used to throw it down the sink - but still don't worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And she bought that did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes. And then we used to have salts - and then in springtime - in springtime, brimstone and treacle. Yes. Yes. Well it used t
o be for - er - brimstone for - er - health reasons - oh yes we used to get right up to standard with - er - health things. Horrible stuff but we had it. If - if - if we were seen throwing it away we had it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did any of your family brew beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No. Mother used to have - I remember mother used to have a bottle - a quart bottle of stout - very reasonable in those days - used to last her a week. She used to have a little drop in a glass like that - and then 'course we'd all say to her can we have
 a little drop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother and father grow their own vegetables and fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, no, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they buy tinned or dried fruit or vegetables ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - very little tinned fruit - wasn't - wasn't that in those days - frui
t was very reasonable in those days and of course we used to buy - we used to go for what they called specked apples and all that sort of thing - specked plums and that and you'd buy two or three pennyworth and that - that used to ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Specked means with a little flaw on it does it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes - sort of an apple with a piece in - used to get a bit cheaper - mum used to cut that off and make her apple pie. And we would have - we had no fruit after lunch - but we would have either an apple or a very small orange on a Sunday after dinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother and father keep any livestock - hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - no, we didn't have the room, no. We had a cat I think, yes. A cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And how many times a week did you eat meat, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Meat? Well - most days 'cos meat was very reasonable in those days and mother used to eke it out quite well with her puddings. Mind, on Mondays we never used to have cold meat, but on the Monday we used to have - mother used to make a very big suet pud
ding - huge big one - and we could either have treacle on that, black treacle, or - it was very reasonable - or we was rather keen on brown sugar and vinegar. Yes - we used to love it - and a big - and - and first of all we used to have a big plate of sou
p
. She'd put a pot with all the old bones and she used to put pea flour in - for about three - threepence or something for a big packet - but it was soup and - er - we used to have a bowl of that, you see, and this huge big pudding, that was enough for us 
then, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember ever having tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Tinned meat? No, I can't remember - no, I don't think we ever did. We might have done - as a treat or some sort, but I can't recall it at all - ever seeing tinned stuff, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit, from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Mother never went - er - mother never - er - we all - we - children come first. Yes. Mothe
r would have some but she'd have very little and we'd say to her oh you haven't had a great deal - well naturally as children we were always hungry - and we was finished ours and all back to school again. But - er - I can remember her plate - er - only be
ing half full to what ours was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father have more food than you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well of course he had his - er - naturally his share - naturally he was a working man and that - well mother was a - poor working woman - but he always had his
 - um - I don't think he was a wonderful big eater but he had - father come first naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat every bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 We had to have - er - every bit that was there and if we didn't have it - it would be put for another meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You couldn't say I only want that or that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well if you don't eat it now you'll have to have it for your tea. Or - or for dinner tomorrow - yes. Naturally we never had it for tea but mother used to - er - never waste it - it was always put on another plate I suppose, and we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So in fact she'd say that but when the time came .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - that's right - it was worked in for another meal - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to w
ait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No we used to say pass the salt please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, you could, and if there was enough - er - then we'd all have a bit more, but if there wasn't enough then - er - then mother'd say no
 that's enough, you've - that's for tomorrow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes. That - that - we had to have table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you have to sit up or ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes. And I - er - know my sister was - on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 equity}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 side - she used to look at me - and I was the ringleader of the lot - and I used to got to her like that - mum she's at it again - and of course I used to get a clout for that. But - er - that was all duri
ng the meal time which shouldn't happen, but did happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And when could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not until we were - we used to say could we leave the table - and mother said sit still til you've finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So if you had finished before the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
You had to wait until they had finished. Unless of course we had a job to do, then she'd say well Edie or Florrie you get up - and you can do so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - yes - but of course not lunch time because the boys - the older boys are out, you see, but they used to come home probably to an evening meal of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And then you'd all sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er -
 well - no. The boys - the older boys would sit in the front room - but we never had - er - a meal after tea. Tea was in the kitchen and that was that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Places? Oh yes, we had to sit at the same place every - yes, yes - sit at the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How was the meal served - who served it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Father used to do the carving and mother used to do the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I suppose from the youngest, I suppose, round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But it was the youngest, not the oldest, first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, the - the youngest first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well - they'd sit at the table or sit on mothers lap probably if they were that - er - small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
If they were small - that small - mother would feed them of course and eat her own meal as best she could - because the other young one the baby - would be in bed, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember about what age they started feeding themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I suppose as soon as ever we were old enough to hold a - er - three or four, I suppose, or before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, she never - she never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 favored}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  one more than the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was she openly affectionate to you, did she ever tell you ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no - but you - you knew if was there - you knew that if you wanted - er - if you'd got a secret sort 
of you you wanted to - er - spurt out, it - mum was there to shoulder it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So if you had worries and things you could share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well I can't remember having worries as a - er - children - we always played together - we wer
e a homely - er - family, we played - we'd fight with other people - children in the mews and come and tell mum what they'd done and so she'd say serve }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 you right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , you shouldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, very easy. I always got on with him very well. But we had to .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, oh yes - we had to do as we were told - there was no second telling - mother used to say now Edie so and so - finish, and I'd say, no - I don't want to do it. That was that - and we had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You could talk to your father easily about things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, they were our parents and we just looked up to them as children shoul
d do I suppose, I don't know how other families go on, but - we were quite happy as family - the whole lot of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well, of course, naturally, we - there was always squabbles here and there and we'd pull one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 hair and all that sort of thing and - er - and if we didn't stop when we was told then of course we could expect a good hiding off - or - or a clout of some sort. I won't tell you again mother said and we knew she meant it. And we didn't do it again.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never heard my mother say that. No, she never said that. Mother was a even - my mothers like me - I go a long 
time before I get upset, but when I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She wouldn't encourage you to fight back if other children hurt you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - if - er - um - people were a bit - oh she used to think you shouldn't have upset them to - er - to fight with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well I suppose as - er - er - she hoped we'd grow up as we did - I mean to say, I think she found out that we all stood on our own feet as she expected us to. Yes, but she never said so -
 she just sort of took it for granted that - I presume that - er - she tried to bring us up in the best way she could and she hoped that we would stay that way. And I presume we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I don't think so - er - as a young girl just going to service mother'd say now take care of yourself - and I knew what she meant - that was all. Goodbye and take care of yourself - mind what you're up to - that sort of thing and we knew t
hat mother ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So they trusted you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Swearing? We were never - we were never allowed to swear - no. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 weren
\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  allowed to swear - if we did say a little rude word and we thought it was very funny mother would only just look at us and say well I heard you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you ever remember your parents swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Never. No, I never heard my parents swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, not when the grown ups were talking. I we butted in mother'd say - just a minute someone's speaking. See, but not with a harsh ....

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well we'd get a hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who would give it you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
My mother mostly and - I remember once - we were in the bedroom and my father's - mother's bedroom backed on - them wooden slats you see, and we were rare ones, at least I was, - er for - er - going on our backs and putting our legs up the 
wall and my father would bang the wall like this and say that's enough of that - morning - early morning mostly and he'd do it twice and we knew that if we didn't stop then and he used - he'd come out and we'd have the strap then. And while I was up there
 I had a lovely bare bottom. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they punish you a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, they warned us and we knew then that if - er - we didn't do it - if we done it a second time we would get into trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you always got punished in the same way - you'd get a good smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, always, always - and I think that's how we learnt to be, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And was it always with a strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, hand mostly. But - er - father - if he come along and he had his strap - he used to wear a leather belt - but -
 er - didn't used to - er - just one flap and we'd know it was there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - the only time that over stood out in my memory as - as a child - um - there was a person that lived in th
e street that took a - well I don't say a fancy to me, but she - give me a shilling once now and again and I had rather long hair which was supposed to have been very nice - right down to my waist - and - er - whenever she see me in the street she'd alway
s
 give me - then Easter time she'd either give me a bag of sweets - it was always me, I don't know why me, but - um - and then Easter time we used to have to go round to her house to collect an Easter egg and it was me again. I'd been naughty - done someth
i
ng - and mother sent me to bed so I thought oh I'm not going to have any Easter egg, you see, so of course I cried my eyes out and - and oh hours I cried - Mother said if you don't stop she said I'll give you the cane or the strap and I thought I cry no m
ore she'll let me go out and get my Easter egg - no she didn't. I always - that stood out in my mind - but anyway she sent my elder sister for it. And said - told her - didn't say I'd been naughty but said that I wasn't well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 fact smack you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes, yes, of course, yes, smacked me and put me to bed. I forget what I done but I done something so she - well no Easter egg, that's that - oh I had Easter egg after, they went and got it. That always stood out in my mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well I suppose we used to think it was - unfair at the time but as you grow older you see that - er - mother was quite right in doing it. Naturally you - you wasn't old enough to - er - to see or to remember tho
se things on her side but naturally when you've been smacked for something you think it didn't ought to happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel that you wanted to hurt them back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no. Never - never embittered. We might probably be a bit sulky about it because we
've been hit but - er - it soon wore off. We were a very, very together family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, mother was w
ith us more, you see, so I suppose - er - father was out all day practically, you see, and - er - meal time father used to come in - we - we'd had our meal - lunch - or dinner time as we used to call it - and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 you see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  mother had to check us then if we were 
doing wrong so - but if father was there and - of course he would take a hand - or if probably mother would say wait until your father comes in and I'll tell him - but she never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well yes I suppose we had some little thing - um - probably the older girls that were in service would give us some little thing, you see, but - er - probably mother might make a little - few extra cakes - but nothing really - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't have anything particularly special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have guests at all on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't have a birthday party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - oh heavens no, never even thought of it. We were a party in ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well - the children didn't used to - I suppose we bought her little things - but it was more - er - the parents giving us little things. I remember Christmas mor
ning we used to have a old black stocking and we'd have an orange put in the toe and probably an apple and a few nuts and my grandmother was in - bedridden - she used to send us a turkey every Christmas and we used to cook it in front of the sitting room 
fire outside hanging on here - like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Outside the fire - twist it round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, yes. And in this parcels she used to send were these little sugar fancy things with - er - shape of a watch with - er - an angel on - all those sort of things. And 
probably older sisters would put a packet of sweets in or - or something wearable - another pair of black stockings - but nothing but - we used to - but that was our Christmas treat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you'd have that in a black stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In black stockings - they always wore black in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you'd each have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you hang it up at the end of the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, yes. And we'd hang it up - wake up two and three hours in the morning and feel what you've got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what happened after that on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Christmas Day we used to have the turkey and - er - we used to go out and play out of mother's way then - and we used to have to help wash up and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, the children did, yes, yes, oh yes we had to go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you a member of the Jewish religion. Your parents were Jewish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no my parents were Christians - oh yes - no me father worked for Jewish people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I thought you said your father was Jewish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, my father worked for Jewish people. No, we were born, I was born in Paddington - well I was born in Paddington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, twice on the Sunday morning and afternoon. Or Sunday school it was called then, probably church in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 evening.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And on Christmas Day what time did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - I don't - don't think there was any different time but we had to go - I know - if it was a Sunday or Christmas Day or anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember - did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well - used to have penny tin whistles or something like that. Well, my - my mother's like that too - go out in the mews and play and of course we - that's what we wanted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you all have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - well I don't say we all had them no, one would have a - probably someone would get a thing a bon-bon, something like that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have a piano in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Piano? What in a room this size?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - my father used to - er - sing his little songs to us sort of thing, and we still remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What were they, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - oh now, wait a minute - man that broke the bank at Monte Carlo - there's 
one and - er - there's a thing he used to say - there was a little sparrow went up the spout - there came a heavy thunderstorm and washed the spadger out.- next thing there came sunshine and dried up all the rain and the twiggy little spadger went out to 
work again. That was always his little - er - bedtime - er - saying to us. Oh lots of little songs he used to sing to us but I can't remember them just at the moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, we used to play - er - hop - back and forth stone we used to call it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes we had comics and - er - and books - er - probably loaned from school, but we didn't have a loan - didn't go to a library.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents have any books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They never read, no. Very seldom - didn't have time really. Used to read a paper probably or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have a newspaper regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well - no, no
t regularly because they couldn't afford it and they used to be - we went out and the older boys - the older boys brought a paper in - well he just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 had it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 . I think he had a Sunday paper always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, News of the World I think, I think the News of the World existed in those days as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember your mother and father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they ever read aloud to you or each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, not that I can recall anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 A funeral? Er - only my sister's that was - er - torpedoed. That's the only one that died, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old were you then - would that be before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - she died at 19 - 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She died in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 1918, yes. That was during the war, the first world war. And that was the only one - the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you all go to her funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well no - you couldn't go to the funeral because she was torpedoed, dear, you see, that's why there was - was - er torpedo on the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 nster{\*\xmlclose}
. So of course we didn't know any more - we went to - to - er - Lady Angles where she was in service and - er - her ladyship said that she'd been down to the quay every day to see if - looking at the bodies that w
ere brought up but - I don't know if they bought up my sister or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was she doing in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leinster}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 {\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well she met - she went first of all to Ireland - er - with the Duchess of Anglesey - the ladies maid was on holiday - and she used to take the housemaid with her when she was on holiday - and my sister was housemaid there. Well when she went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - she went to Guiness's people - she made friends with this Alf there and they said if ever she wanted to come back she could come back for a hol
iday. So she went for a holiday, when her holiday was due and unfortunately, she had I think she had a fortnight, or I don't know how long a holiday she did have, but she wrote to the housekeeper and asked if she could have a few extra days. And they were
 so busy at the house in Staffordshire that the housekeeper said no, she was awfully sorry, but she would have to come back at her said time. And unfortunately the day she come back that was it. Got torpedoed. 'Course she felt it very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - she was older than me - let me think now - what when she died? Now you're asking, now. Er - wait a minute - think back - she was six - six years - seven years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 You\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  be about twenty-four so she'd be about thirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Thirty - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But apart from that you can't remember any funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, nobody died, nobody passed away in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you taken out visiting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 neighbors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Very seldom - very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you did go who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I can't remember even going to visit relatives. 'Cos mother's relatives - I think my father...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I thought you said you remembered going to see your grandparents in Bedfordshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Well that was on just an occasion, 
probably on a holiday, once two or three years and she'd take two or three of us then and she used to go stop in my grandfathers cottage and we'd all go, I suppose, all of us - about four of the younger ones you see. Probably the two youngest wasn't born 
then, you see. We were about six or seven - about three or four of the children used to go - but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you taken shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. We used to have to do the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never remember going out with me father at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember any other outings with your parents - bank holidays and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. We never went out because we couldn't afford it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever go away for a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - 
no, not the children, but when we were in service and we had a holiday then then we - 'cos we had a little money then and then we used to go away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Apart from going to see your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no holidays, not as children anyway, not until we went to service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you went to see your grandparents didn't you say your mother occasionally took two or three of you with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And how long would you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Probably a week or.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you say that was a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes - that would be a holiday to use being in the country like, after playing in the mews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So what you mean by not going on holiday is that you didn't go to the sea side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well we never went away apart from that. Until we were old enough to be in service and pay our way and then had a holiday. Had me holiday once a year then as you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So after you went into service at fifteen or sixteen did you go away then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, we used to go away, my sister together, probably, we went for a week or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Saturdays - just doing odd jobs for mother and then shopping and then out to play in the mews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you always stayed in the mews to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Always in the mews or out in the street. And we used to go up the street sometimes and - er - there used to be a greengrocers up the top there and we used to tie a cotton on his knocker a
nd stand across the road and knock his knocker. Until he found us out, so we couldn't do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Sundays - well we used to have to go to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the morning or afternoon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Both - morning and afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - usually about an hour and a half something like that and time we got to school and had our little prayers and that and then of course time for lunch - playing in the meantime - went again in the afternoon - and if we were o
ld enough had to go to church in the evening time - that was our Sundays passed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes - we wore our best clothes, yes. Yes, wore our best clothes on Sundays. Whatever they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your parent didn't think it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. We played games we just - we were happy - we just did what we liked. So long as we weren't - er - a nuisance, sort of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents go to church or any place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never remember them going - they might - no I don't think they ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What denomination were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What do you mean Christians - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 Christians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were they Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Church of England - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose} of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - no, not in that day, not in that day - but we used to have - er - a prize for - er - what they used to call it now - prize giving, yes, 'cos I've got a Bible now that I had for my prize. It would be 
- er - attendances book - by being - attending the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you didn't actually go out for an outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What other social activities }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 organized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  by the church or the Sunday school did you take part in, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I'm just
 trying to think - I remember - I don't know if it was the day school or Sunday school - I think it was a Sunday school outing I went to once - and we went to Brickett Wood if I remember right. Yes, that was the Sunday school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where's Brickett Wood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Now you've asked me something now haven't you. I'm a Londoner and I don't know where it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old were you, do you remember, on this outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well we were still at school so I must have been about ten or eleven I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the church that you went to run any temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Temperance club - not that I know of, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you belong to any other club }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 organized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, we had to say grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - father started and we'd all have to say it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, we weren't - didn't have to say that. As long as at lunch time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have family prayers together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. In service yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In service you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes - when I was with Bridgemans when - before he was Home Secretary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 William Bridgeman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - about twenty-four twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not between these years before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no, no. This was later years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember between the ages of fifteen and eighteen did you .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was in service - yes, different jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you can't remember family prayers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. We didn't have family prayers until we got to the Bridgemans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh that I can't remember, I mean to say, we weren't old enough I suppose to know what politics were in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, he was - no. Didn't interest us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, not that I know of. They might have done but of course in those days one doesn't - children didn't think about politics - er - the parents take interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You wouldn't know if they were left wing or right wing or Tory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, never heard of it - no - the only wing I know is wing of a chicken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They might have done but I can't remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you wouldn't know what party they voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers - do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
I never heard anything about it. I mean to say if - if anything like that happened he wouldn't say it in front of the children. He would just discuss it with mother, I presume, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your father wasn't a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Mother - well - when mother had five minutes she used to do our mending. Do our mending - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She didn't go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Never went outside the door from one weeks end to another and that was Saturday night as I told you. She went to get - the Sunday joi
nt - reasonable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Father - we - I don't think he ever went out either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He didn't go to the pub or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - he'd go out for a drink. Once - very seldom - once now and again - if by if by chan
ce my mother's brother - oh no - his brother come - he was a butler in Berkeley Square - and if he come down to see us sometime then they'd go and have a drink together. That's the only time I remember - we had a public shop in the mews. That's the only t
ime I ever remember him going to a pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who? Mum? The only interest she had was fetching us in from outdoors. No, poor mum, it's terrible isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes, when - the only time she went out to enjoy herself was when we were old enough to take her to a music hall. And then we'd say oh come on mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was that before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that was before 1918 when we were just old enough sort of to enj
oy her - but only when we were in service when we could afford to pay for the both, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And where did you go, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - Old Metropolitan in - er - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Edgware Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I think she'd get in there f
or about threepence, something like that. It was - er - not bad. Used to have Gertie Miller and all those sort of things. It was all - er - that type of artists - er singers and - er - woman singers - Marie Lloyd.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You saw her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, Marie Lloyd - yes - she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 marvelous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  really, Marie Lloyd, Hetty King - er - crowds of others, I can't remember at the moment who they were but - and they had ventriloquist - er - acts and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Could you have a drink in the interval or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, we never even thought about it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother enjoy the music}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Enjoy the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 music hall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - yes, of course, naturally, I mean to say, she went just once now and again, it wasn't very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What time? Er - well - all times really because sometimes if the carriage was ordered in the afternoon - er - they might probably go out to teas some - his ladies might go out for tea sometimes - or when the
 time he come home he'd got his horse to see to and his carriage to see to to clean and horse to feel and it would be any time, just depend on what time he was finished with the - taking the people out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What would be the earliest he would get home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose about six or seven I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the latest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh sometimes he'd have to take them to a theatre, you see, then I wouldn't know be when he come 'cos we would be in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Be quite late though, wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, every evening apart from that - he never went out anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Only just that - if anyone come like his brother, he was a butler, and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But he wouldn't go out by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. Mother never went inside the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Father? No. Had no time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He didn't go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He - he used to like betting on a horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He liked betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He didn't actually go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, oh - he couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But he did like to bet on a horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He might have sixpence each way on - if he - if he could afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was that a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well - yes we had to go out sometimes and get him a racing paper - that was his only - er - one activity that I can recall and - then if he won - er - well I can say mother would benefit by it - not much of course - er - 
if he - if he lost well that - er - he couldn't do it again 'cos he hadn't got any more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother mind him doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I don't know - dare say it was the only bit of frivolity he had so she didn't - er - mind so long as us children didn't go short.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother and father belong to any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
They might have done, but not that I - er - I tell you there wasn't enough money in the family to - er - in the house to put money by so she'd try to encourage us when we
 were small to - er - sixpence here and there in the Post Office savings bank, if we had it, if we were given sixpence by anybody. My uncle used to give us - well we didn't have sixpence in those days - penny that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They didn't belong to any clubs incase your father was ill or towards funeral expenses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
There was nothing - nothing like that available - I suppose there was but - er - no - under the circumstance we couldn't - she couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh very well at times, and fight like all the children do and we'd fight back again and then we'd be friends for a little while and then fight back again as children do - when they're a big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No - I was particularly close to my sister that died - but then of course she was a lot older and I used to see her a great deal - which - we were very close together - in fact I was supposed to be the living image of her. When we went to colle
ct her things after her death - er - Lady Anglesey - I went up with my sister to see Lady Anglesey and she was of course full of tears 'cos she thought a lot of my sister - and she asked the butler to ask me to go up again because I was - she wanted to se
e me again because I was so much like her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And she was the one you felt closest to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - I could show you a photograph of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 As a child - who did you play with - your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Brothers sisters and the other children in the mews. Other neighbours, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Just the ones in the mews?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did you play, you told me in the mews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the mews on in the street. Never went far from home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You weren't allowed to go far?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about in other people's gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well - everybody had gardens in those days were of course better class people - we weren't allowed in other people's gardens. If we did we'd get into trouble. Mother used to hear of it - used to pick flowe
rs as - you know - when we go to school - send the dog after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh we played a thing called tin-can-wally. That was an old tin can - used to throw it up the street - one - one of us used to be - had to hide our eyes and
 we used to throw the can up the street and then we used to run and hide - all the rest of us hide and the fellow who'd got the can had to come backwards so that he couldn't see us where we hid - hide and then we'd say - if he thought we were anywhere he'
d bang the tin on the floor and say tin-can-wally, I can see so and so you're in so and so. And if we never used to answer then he'd have to come and find us - if we got there - back before he did he'd have to go up again. Silly - but it was fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember any other games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - we'd play skipping and - er - we used to have hoops, iron hoops with the skimmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What's a skimmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 An iron - just a iron - a fine iron ring and a skimmer is a - a - got a small handle with a - just a hook
 on it - and you bowl the hoop and you put the skimmer underneath and it used to go along on its own - but you'd have to keep it on the thing - keep it going, while you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 re running. We used to go all round the houses then - we used to have wooden hoops and all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember any other games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - hide and seek of course and playing with the - er - mostly hiding seek I think it was, I can't remember any other games, I suppose we did play - I think we played snakes and ladders and all that sort of thing indoors but not outdoors, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, mother didn't mind us getting dirty - but we had to be clean when we come in of course. We wasn't supposed to get dirty but
 we did, but mother wouldn't say look how filthy you are. No, no. Unless you were very bad of course. You'd get a good scrubbing then. With Lifebuoy soap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you belong to any youth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13438853\charrsid10431346 organizations}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
There was none in those days, not that I know of. It's only the children of today that want a lot of amusement that - er - these youth clubs 
come up. Wasn't any youth clubs to go to even when I was in service. I suppose there were in a sense but I didn't hear of them, we had no time. Only time I got when I come home was pop in and see mum we'd have half a day a week and we'd had to do our - er
 - when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 I had to lay me table before I ever went. I'd get home about three or finish me work about three get home about four - always went home to see mum - then go and meet a boy friend afterwards and be in by ten, so there wasn't much ti
me to go to youth clubs - want the fresh air we had once a week - only get it once a week and every other Sunday. Then we had to do our work before we went out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you spend your free time when you were at school? Did you have any particular hob
bies - apart from going out and playing did you keep any pets or collect anything or do any gardening or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. We had just a cat at home and that was just run around and used to feed it and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - no, not in our younger days - only hobby was just - er - helping mother. They were our hobbies - looking after the younger children - but we didn't - er - usually come amiss because we knew how to do it - we never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 quibbled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes, we - if we went into the park mother would pack us up sometimes - er - if the weather was nice - two or three of us - with some bread and dripping and a bottle of water and we used to get a line on a piece of string and fish
 tiddlers out of the pond, that's all I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you go for walks at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well - when we older, I mean, several of you wanted to get away from the other kids we'd go probably for walks. But that was only when we were in service, sort of thing, we just played around and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have a bicycle when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No. Not us. All we enjoyed was getting on the back of the mail cart. And having a ride on that - if we could. As long as mother didn't see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you take part in any sports, as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Um - well no, not the girls. The boys were allowed to - um - perhaps play cricket at school and swimming but the - us girls wasn't allowed to. We wasn't mother didn't - er - see eye to eye about us girls going swimming. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 organized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  sports at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes I think I heard the boys say that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But not the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose there were but - er - not as regards hockey or anything like that. Oh no, there was nothing like th
at. But there was a swimming - er - afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Nothing like that while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No. Er - we used to cadge on dad when he got paid - we used to say dad can we have a ha'penny - and he used to say - used to take us a whole hour to get - get a ha'penny - sometimes he would let us have one and
 we used to get no end of sweets for a ha'penny - my, oh my, liquorice braids and aniseed balls and I don't know what we didn't used to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you didn't have regular pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, oh no. If we were good probably we'd have a ha'penny - bu
t a h'penny was - was a - that was - but you could buy quite a lot in those days for a ha'penny or penny. Ha'penny was quite enough for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family? Relations or friends or neighbours did they help her at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't say they helped in any way as regards to - you mean in regards - er - the family -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well would they come and give her a hand to do things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well my mother had a baby - she always had them, home }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7152263\charrsid10431346 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  and then she used to have a woman in all the time - I forget what they used to call them now - they had some name - but she used to come in every morning and - er - at night time and do washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You'd have to pay her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, no, no. We'd pay her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well we used to rally round but mother was never - never had time to be ill. She didn't. She had - she used to suffer like I do with me throat and I've seen her walk around half dead before she'd give in. She'd have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 quinsy\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember actually being so ill that she had to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - never known her to go - only when she's had the babies. And I can't remember that 'cos the babies would come after me, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do
 you remember what would happen when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born - do you remember the sort of procedure. I mean your mother had them at home didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes. Had them at home, yes. And the doctor was sent for and the doctor would say, "What again }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Tyler." And then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 Hooker, that's the woman I remember, was sent for and she'd come and do the washing and she'd have to put big boiler on our little stove and do all washing sheets and everything - keep us girls - get our foo
d - what she got for that I wouldn't know - but she was a nice woman - I remember her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long did she stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh all day. There until early morning and see us off to school and - er - soon as mother could of course, naturally, she'd be up and do
ing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many days would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well in those days I think they used to keep them in bed for a - well over a week - week or a fortnight. Now of course they get you up almost next day, don't they - not in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They probably needed the rest though, she had so much to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well you see she was sixty-eight when she died, see that photograph, and I'm seventy-five, the difference, just absolutely worn - then I think she had three three or four mis-carriages. My father told me that. Can't say it on there though can I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well - er - no - er - they're mostly in the country except my father's brother as I said - was this butler and he used to come and see him, that's the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In Berkeley Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Berkeley Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - we had some relatives I think lived further afield, but - er the had their problems the same as us probably I suppose and we didn't see a great deal of them, once now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you see much of your father's brother that was a butler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes he was - we often used to see him - he used to come on his days off and pop round and see us and bring mother a little something of what he could afford to - and he was very good to us that way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 As regards}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  food and that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Only next door neighbours they were very friendly with, oh yes, and if anything wanted they'd call in if mother - probably mother was sick or something - expecting and she'd have a pain fit and they'd fetch in the person next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So she would come in and give a hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, she was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And do you remember, were they the only sort of close friends your parents had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, there were several - we wer 
all - nearly all the people in the mews were - er - rally round if the occasion arose - but - um - we never seemed to - er - mum used to get over her - er - whatever it was herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they share the same friends - your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes w
e all - if we see them in the mews - you see, we're such a - er - a completely sort - about a dozen houses down there that we knew everybody down there and - and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother have any particular friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I think the perso
n next door was more friendly than anything - she'd - if anything happened - or with us - she naturally, if she wanted any help she'd say send one of the children in for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Wood, I think her name was, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Wood next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Very seldom - but as I say there was no room to - er - to ask anybody. They'd had so much to do all day long that - er - time was fairly occupied with the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 If they ever were - say they came for some reason, would they be offered something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well yes I suppose - a cup of tea or something like that if they did come, but we were out most of the time so we didn't - can't remember who used to come in. I don't think so, because we would have remembered it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends - if they did come in - or father's friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - must have been mother's friends mostly, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And neighbours - would they pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - they would probably come and knock at the door and - well call up the stairs - we used to come up wooden stairs - and they'd call }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Tyler - if she wanted to know something or if one of the nei
ghbours was very handy with the needle and if mother had something to do she'd run up for one of us children so it was handy you see. But more often than not they'd just have a chat on the stairs. Mother - I think for the simple reason mother had no time 
to - er - with all us lots to - er - to spare much time for outsiders you see, she used to go half way down the stairs and that was that. And talk to them on the stairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember your parents ever going out together to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements - what do you think your parents did when they got together if ever.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Made, babies, I suppose. Oh, it's gone on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I was going to say with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, they never went out - I tell you mother never went outside the door so ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups - in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What in the family? What in service? Well only the people we worked for. Naturally in - they were in our estimation they were higher than what we were or we wouldn't have gone to work for them, you see, but we went to work as I say, from eleven years old.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you thought of yourself as working class and them as a higher class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. That's right. Because they had the money to pay us to do their work for them. That's how its been all along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you just say there were - what different classes were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Just a - just a - no - just a little higher than what we were, I suppose, you see, moneyed people that can afford to have a - well - just me working for them sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about middle classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well middle classes probably would be when we first went to service, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The people you would work for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. And then - well - our middle class from posh people - well we thought they were posh naturally, but we weren't allowed to say or do as we liked with 'em - we had to do as we was told even then. In service.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Average, I suppose, I wouldn't - never even thought about it to tell you the truth. I'm just one of the many, I suppose, ju
st one of the thousands that used to earn a living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I hope its not....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, I don't mind you asking, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think of yourself as working class or lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Working class, no, working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of people belonged to the same class group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of people? Same people I suppose that earn a living like myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 People in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Service or - er - of course in those days it was service, you didn't think of anything else. But now of cou
rse - service - people for service is all gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What for instance would you say about shop owners, would they be the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well they would be a better class than what we were because they got the money to afford to - er - well middle - you'd cal
l the middle class wouldn't you. But I never worked in a shop so - me brothers and that of course naturally did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember being brought up to treat people of on sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, we - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you for instance be taught to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 We were taught to respect people we were working for. Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you ever told to curtsy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Or touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. But in service 'course - no, no, no. My father always touched his cap when he was - er - people come in or out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have any other way in which you had to show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - so long as you done your work and you respected the people you worked for and - they made no complaints you were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there anyone you called Sir, Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, everybody you called Sir - I even still got the habit - I still call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Inglis Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Everybody you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Madam. Yes. Except titled people and then you had to say Sir this or Lady - 
er - your lordship or your ladyship - which I never came in for - but my sister did you see, two of my - both my sisters worked for titled people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in those ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well no, because I mean t
o say, mother wasn't doing anything for anybody. If you did a - a service for anybody well you know those people were - er - a little bit higher than you were to be able to pay you to do it. But mother of course never did anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who were the most important people in the district where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the district? - Er - well I imagine no - no important people actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't remember anybody particularly famous or important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, not round where we lived, not where 
we lived. We thought the people my father worked for were naturally well above average actually because of him being employed by them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who were they - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They were - er - a Jewish family called Lewis and he was with 'em - oh 't
il he retired. Then there was me - then I got a job from one friend - McCutter which was another Jewish people - it was my first job in service - I was about fifteen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Shopkeepers? Well oh about - they were quite average, used to go and buy your things and say thank you and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What the shopkeepers? Well I wouldn't know that - no - well what - who they associated with, I mean to say, we were sent for our errand and that was that. Paid for it and thanked them and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The clergy? I don't think they ever come round to see mother, at all, I can't remember them ever coming round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, they never come to
 see people. If there's anything wrong at school or something like that then the headmistress would send a note round to say - er - I'd done something wrong or - or something else can happen at school, we'd be late at school then something like that but n
othing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Employers? They associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well, I mean to say, the only one I associated with - with Lutyens with his work designing but - er - but Bridgeman, of course, I was with him, but he wasn't in office - Home Secretary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they associate with friends of their own class do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes. They were title people I think that - er - in the family - and of course naturally they - er - had dinner parties and had different people - title people sometimes and vice versa that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of people would you say went to the church in your district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well just the middle class - er - us children people had to go with other people but - er - the majority of the - Paddington }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Borough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  where the church was used to go, you see, people that had got the houses that we used to do the steps for you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there a chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There was a chapel but I believe that was - er - away from us - er - we went to a church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't remember the sort of people that went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Where you lived did all the people in the same class as yourself have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, they was all the same standard - always working - husband always we
nt out to work - and mothers never went out to work in those days - woman never had to work in those days. They all just earned an average wage I suppose that was average in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you feel they were all.....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 All much of - what we knew in the mews - all much about the same. And all friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The same group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think one group felt itself superior to the rest, was there any family for instance or group of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I suppose if some of the people 
in the mews had - was earning more money or the family was getting more money, they might have been a little more outstanding than what we were but - it was never shown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think that some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well yes, some families were a little bit more - er - sort of - one family had two boys, cos they used to fight like blazes with them two. But - no - I don't suppose the parents was any different to ours. No there wasn't any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There was no one is more rough and one more respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember any distinction between craftsmen and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 laborers}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I - I no. The only thing I can remember years back when there was a lot of out of work and the people us
ed to come round the streets singing about being out of work, I can just slightly remember that. I can't remember what year that was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother and father have the same attitude towards people in different classes, do you thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well, I suppose so, as I say I don't remember them even getting in contact with anybody. If by chance - er - when I first went into a small job and Used to - er - nothing in it - er - if I didn't want to go back I said no I 
don't think I want to go back I won't go back the old lady used to go round to mother and - er my mother would say I'll see she does come back sort of thing and she sort of hold the piece between 'em - between the both of us, and I used to go back again. 
I had to go back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think your mother and father would both sort of think the people you worked for were a higher class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , yes, oh yes, because they had money, well, more money than we had. They could afford to - er -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, mother was just - er - an everyday working - working woman - just lived for her family - I think that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Move from one class to another? What we? No I don't think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well I suppose, actually, there would be some people in the street, if they got - the husband got a better job to go to he would naturally take it. But 
then I wouldn't know anything about that. We'd - that wouldn't interest us you see, 'cos we had nothing to do with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You can't remember anyone who did that, moved upwards from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I can't recall anybody like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - yes, I've often heard it said - oh he's a real gentleman - but any - er - individual, one individual I can't recall, but - er - I myself even now say oh he's a through ge
ntleman because he's got such good manners and that sort of thing you see, you meet different people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So why do you think, just a question of manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, yes I suppose so, I mean to say after all' said we're human beings and if one person can
't treat a person as another human being I must say - that's all wrong I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 A police? Oh yes, he used to see if us children weren't doing any damage which we used to do of 
course. Used to break windows and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they come round regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Oh, very seldom see anybody, they just come round because.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was it just one policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Only one at a time then, it's only recent years that th
ere's two - er - we lived in peaceful times let me tell you. We certainly did - we never heard any burglar - I suppose there was burglars but we never heard of any like you do these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you know the policeman - did you know him by sight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 O
h yes, we knew - not as regards in Paddington - but - er - when we moved to Marylebone - my husband got to know several of them and we got to know them and then there was the police buildings here when we come here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But not when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, no. We used to be afraid of them because we knew very well if we did anything wrong they'd - er - they'd go and tell mother or something - we'd get into trouble, we were scared of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, she'd say she'd call a policeman but she never did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well when we saw - mind, I never saw him arrest anybody or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was he friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well we never used to talk to hi
m 'cos we were scared of him. Of course. We saw police and we thought ooh they're after us. But they wasn't but we thought they were because we thought we'd done something wrong, you see. And we were scared - run off indoors, good and quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. Six shillings a week rent. Father earned twenty-six shillings a week as wages - and bought up the family - us family that's - mind you the older boys were out working up to - how many of then - five or six of us - seven of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no I never did. I don't know who was the landlord. No. Not as a - not as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh of course they had to. Fair enough, otherwise we wouldn't have to go out to work to do doorsteps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think about it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I suppose we didn't like the idea of going out but.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, about your parents finding it difficult - did you ever think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, we didn't think about it because we knew very well that - er - well that was that and we had to get on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 It didn't worry you - did you ever look at your mother and feel sorry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I - we used to feel sorry that mother never wen
t out - out more than she did do and I feel sorry that she hadn't - well I suppose we wouldn't have thought it in our younger days but when we were old enough to realize naturally we thought about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you said earlier that your father was never out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was he ever ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, he had - er - in his - when I was a service in - he had enteric fever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - I was about seventeen I suppose, seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Obviously he was off work for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What difference did that make to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well - I wouldn't know that 'cos I didn't know if he got paid - I never asked questions - and mother wouldn't tell us anything like that - I was in service and I
 only used to go home for a couple of hours a day and naturally mother wouldn't pour out her troubles to us, so I don't....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you notice any difference when you whet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I couldn't tell you 'cos whether his employers paid him while he was qu
eer or whether - I suppose there was some insurance of some sort in those days, I don't know, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever get help from the Guardians of the Parish or from any charity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. And we never had homework from school to do. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Four or five I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you first started what time in the morning did you go? And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - nine o'clock 'til twelve and then off from twelve to two and then from two 'til four or half past - half past four I think it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you went back to afternoon school at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 2}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}two o'clock{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Two o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What kind of school was it? Board, private, church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Church school, yes - we paid tuppence - tuppence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was it boys or girls or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - it was - er - wasn't mixed together, but the boys section was one section and the girls another, and infants were round the 
corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Walk - wasn't far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 About ten minutes. I went - if we run behind a cart we used to got there in five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh usually my sister and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Your elder sister or your younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
My elder - 'cos the two boys younger than me. And sometimes if the boys were going, but the boys used to keep to themselves and - if I was doing some doorsteps or me sister doing doorsteps and I wasn't of course we'd go on y
ou see - she'd have to carry on. Chase to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did you have your mid-day meal - you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You told me what you had to eat - you had.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Meat pies, everything substantial - stew - er - real stew with plenty of d
umplings in and - er - plenty of good wholesome, wholesome food we had. We had plenty of vegetables and that and as I said different people gave us and we used to buy cheap fruit - mother used to make - always make something of it of some sort.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Awful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 emphasize}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  certain things as important in life like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, yes we had to do - er
 - there was discip - we had to be - er - discipline in the class but - er - I used to talk when I shouldn't do and then I - it used to be great fun - in our class I used to be in the back row and we looked round on Howe Road on the trains because of cour
se when we was naughty we had to stand with our hands on our head and turn with our back to the class. Well of course I was alright 'cos I was looking out the - looking at the trains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the teachers emphasize manners, tidiness, punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, no, I don't think the teachers taught us that - I mean to say it was home used to teach us to be - er }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7152263\charrsid10431346 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  to have manners - if we weren't - I mean to say if we were bad mannered in school, then of course we'd be reprimanded for it, oh yes of course.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about things like tidiness and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Tidiness? Oh well we had to put our books and all that away and - er - had to be a certain amount tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, must be on time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about ways of speaking, did they pull you up about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well when you're reading of course naturally - er - they were teaching us and if we didn't pronounce our words properly then they'd pull us up about it. It wasn't an - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 emphasized}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  thing - it was - er - we had to read a certain thing and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well we wouldn't get boxed on the ears like mum would do but - er - we'd have to come out or stand on - we'd have to 
stand on - on the - we had desks - long desks for about three or four of us - we had to stand on the seat and turn with our back to the teacher - which took me to looking out the window, which being in the back row always I used to look out the window whi
ch I thought I thought it was rather fun to look out the railway and see everybody passing by so I didn't mind being smacked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long did you have to stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, until teacher thought it was - er - enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did they punish the children apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - we had - er - stand in the corner or else - er - stay in after school and write so many lines 'I must - er - I must behave myself' about fifty lines you used to scrub that off in about ten minutes, couldn't understand it but it was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about things like actually hitting you or anything like that, did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, very seldom - unless we were very - er - very bad - very unruly - and then we'd have to go in front of the headmistress and she would reprimand you bu
t - er - nothing ever really come of it - she never - no - they very seldom hit - I don't think I ever remember our teacher hitting us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they punish the girls in the same way as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, boys were in a different school to what we were 
- they were in the adjoining school - but the boys and girls were not together - was only just a girls school and the boys school was just further up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you hear about the boys being punished in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, except for me brothers -
 if they'd done anything, you see - they used to come home and said - er - nag about their teachers and what they didn't do - and we used to talk about ours - sort of - a friendly get together about school - we hated it none the more for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of things would make you be punished at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well not - er - attending to what - er - teachers was telling you, or - er - spying on the next girl if you could - cheating, which was natural everybody used to do if they - especially for exams - i
f we were caught well we had to come out and all that sort of thing but we never got really repri - you know, punished for it. Word from our teacher was quite enough. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - I don't thi
nk - we didn't have to do any homework but if we had - er - a problem and we used to ask mother about it she'd try and tell us in the best way but she never - er - sort of - um - as children do today, take home homework and have to do a certain amount - n
o, there was nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't have to do homework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, no, no. No homework at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your parents ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Oh yes, they were interested in what you'd done, naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they ever visit the school? Or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I don't - they had no occasion to - not like today, of course, the mothers have to go up every so often to see how their boys are getting on, no - it was a - free and - it was a young free and easy life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, I sup - I suppose so - we - were all poor - poor - it was a church school and - poor people around - living around our road and that - the school was in Howe Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I didn't notice that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Oh, one or two girls were more friendly with some girls than others. One girl I know I couldn't
 stand - she used to chase me home - that's the only girl I didn't like in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And they didn't form up into gangs or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no. We never even thought of that in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I don't think so - I don't er - remember - everybody seemed to be doing just the same - there'd be trouble here and trouble there sort of thing and - er - nothing much come of it - we were - we were - punished or taken in front of the head teacher
 - headmistress and that was it - and it was finished with. We'd have a giggle about it afterwards I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. That was the only school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That was the only school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not quite fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 We had no opportunity - er - you just left and we were bumped into service straight away. Mother....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Looking back on it now, if you had had the opportunity would you have stayed longer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no, because I didn't like school that much. We had no choice so that - it didn't come amiss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you have any regrets about your educations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I've got no regrets, I mean to say, I would now - in later life you - er - I would like to have been a bit more better educated - but as it was in those days one had to take it as it come. One was satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh yes, I mean to say, certainly - we used to know - we used - they used to try and teach us history and - er - and geography - but - er - it didn't sink in very far - which was - they didn't 
sort of bother that much - they - we didn't have to do homework to - er - to remind us that we got to do that sort of thing, we just was taught a certain thing and - er - we were supposed to remember it - if we didn't remember it we'd get in trouble - but
 - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of things did they concentrate on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
I don't know - history and different parts of the country and all that sort of thing and - er - India and what was the capital of India and all those sort of things but - er - I can't remember what they are now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You told me earlier that you did have some part time jobs while you were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes - I was doi
ng - yes, I said I had to go round - my sister and I had to go and wash doorsteps for about sixpence a week, two or three times a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was that all the way through your school life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That was from - from about twelve - eleven or twelve - and onwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you get that particular part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well different people in the street - er - would - er - see us playing around or - probably know mother - no they wouldn't know mother because mother never went out - and - er - they jus
t ask us if we would be able to - would I ask mother if we were able to come and do the doorsteps for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you'd ask your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, yes, of course, oh yes, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So what exactly did you do, you cleaned the doorstep, did they provide you with the cleaning materials?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, yes. Yes, it was mostly hearthstone in those days, big flagstones that had to be whitened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Whitened every time you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Every - oh yes. There used to be three or four steps at the top, then a - er - flagstones all down to the gate and then a step there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many steps - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh - half a dozen sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And how wide?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well - how wide - now you're asking me now, aren't you? Er - well - as doorsteps are today - the width of the doorstep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Fairly large front door and doorsteps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right. But it - they wasn't sort of tiled - it was all just hearthstone in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well it just depends - sometimes you were -
 if you were a bit late going - 'course you had to hurry and get back in time for school, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But about how long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Quarter of an hour, I suppose, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you do it on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, oh no, no, we didn't do it Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes. About sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And obviously they didn't give you any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well, there wasn't even called that - had a holiday when we were children really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel that was fair, sixpence a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh that went to mother - mother had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But at the time, do you remember, did you think sixpence a week was fair?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well, I suppose it was in those days - we - was - we didn't argue, I mean to say, it was just that - er - they - it was g
iven to us and that was that, as - but of course sixpence went an awful long way, you know, in those days. I mean my father only used to earn twenty-six bob - twenty-six shillings a week and six shillings used to come out of that for rent - may be sure wo
uldn't put - didn't go very far with all us lot - so sixpence in mothers pocket was - er - a big help. It - it would buy several pounds of potatoes and lot of veg and bread and whatnot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What would the money be spent on - would it be pooled in the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, mother had it and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
How did you get on with the other people you worked with, I mean your sister was the other person that was cleaning doorsteps with you, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well, I mean to say, she was older than me - by the time I started she was in a better job, you see, she....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So it would be one at a time then, so to speak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh very well, yes, they used to - er - bring us a nice hot pail of water
 - bring it to the door 'cos wasn't allowed inside, sort of thing, and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you feel about your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh some of them were very nice and - er - well I think - I think that everybody - if we didn't like it we'd say to mother
 well, no, I don't like going there, but it - that occasion never arose - we were brought up to be sociable to everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the actual work - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, can't say you exactly liked washing doorsteps on a cold morning, come off it. Case of having to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the job in anyway alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No. We just sort of rushed to school - a piece of - probably - a piece of bread and dripping in our hand and - that's that. 'Cos we hadn't got time to eat it a
t home so we used to nip off quick to school sort of and got inside the school door by nine o'clock and that's all we bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you do any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - not before I left school. But after I left scho
ol I went into a small job - er - just daily and - er - come home at night until they asked they said - well - would I sleep in and that was about ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And was that your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. That was round about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what exactly was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Just domestic cleaner of a flat - er - with two elderly ladies - well one elderly lady and her daughter. And it used to - used to amuse me 'because she always had a barrel of beer and of a night time she would have a hot - hot glass of be
er for her supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 This first job you took you started off daily and very soon started to live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many servants were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Only myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Only yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Uh - huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did you sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - where - at this place? Er - in the - er - basement. In the basement. And the kitchen was on the level too, so I had my meals there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you ate there? Not with the ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Mm - mm. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And is that where you sat when you weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. That's right, yes, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the mistress's supervise all the housework personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, oh yes. She used to say what was to be done - it was a routine job - you had - each day come along you had different jobs to do. I
 remember there - er - they had - in their front sitting room - they had a very big wide window sill and I used to have to kneel out on there, sideways, to clean the windowsill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did you and the other two ladies address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They used to call me - my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  name - Edith - in fact mostly they used to call me Florence because my sister had already been there previous to me. All my sisters - four sisters - went to the same job when they first left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel that they were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, I suppose they were or they wouldn't have employed me - they knew me mother you see, so - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the ladies of the house give any sort of moral guidance to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so. Me mother just told us what we should do and what we shouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you allowed any time to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er yes - I was allowed out most evenings after tea to go home to see our mother which we
re only just walking distance round the corner. And I used to - even then still play out in the mews - not exactly play out in the mews - but be out in the mews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the ladies of the house mind what you did then or when you came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, so long as I was in by - cleaning by nine o'clock, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They didn't really mind what you did in that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What after nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, beforehand. When you went out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, they just - no - they knew I was going to me mothers so that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever feel homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - if they got a bit fractious with me and - the old lady was rather a - er - trouble some person but - er - of course I can see now that it wasn't - I should have given way, but of course I didn't realize in tho
se days, and then I used to go home and tell my mum I wasn't going back again. And then the old lady used to come round and - to my mother - and - er - explain things and of course I had to go back again. That was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were you lonely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes, in a sense, I mean to say. I was the only person there - there was nothing much to do - but - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - I - I didn't actually like that sort of job because it was - er - not a v
ery nice job really, I mean to say, it was a person that - er - a poorish place but one had to do it and that was it. I didn't like it - not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did the housework go - for instance did you send the washing out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, we used to have to do all the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You did it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Just you by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er no. The - er - daughter used to do it - everything - the daughter and I used to do it - mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who made or mended the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Theirs? The daughter I suppose, I didn't have anything to do with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose they were - but all the time I was there they never had any - very old place - dilapidated place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There were no children so where wasn't a nanny there or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did the two ladies eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In their own sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What cooking equipment was there in the house? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Equipment? I think it was a gas - a gas stove. There was - was a very old stove there but I don't think they ever used it much, it was just and old - a gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when breakfast was eaten, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - round about - nine o'clock, I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would both ladies have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what sort of things they ate for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can't remember what they ate, but I know I didn't have much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were any of the following made in the house - bread, jam, bottled fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Made? No, nothing at all. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they grow their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. It was only a small flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many times a week did they eat meat - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Eat meat? Oh I think as far as I know, most days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they or didn't they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 used tinned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Tinned? Er - well tinned stuff wasn't - hadn't come into - er - vogue or whatever you call it, in those days, it was - meat was very reasonable and - er - it was able - easy to get - until of course the war started and then it was very difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have the same food as they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you say you didn't have much of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not - for a breakfast - well a fair amount - but breakfast was never a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I should think you needed breakfast didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, well I expect there was plenty of bread and butter and jam and whatever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 After your job with the two ladies what was the next job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The ne
xt job - I went into - er - a place where father's people - er - brought me - with a staff of about six - and I was a kitchen maid, and I had to get up early in the morning and do a huge big kitchen range which was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9776287\charrsid10431346 black leaded}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  and - er - that was done bef
ore, naturally, before breakfast and then there was a huge - er - long hall to be cleaned and a front doorstep that had - that wasn't hearthstone as a matter of fact - I think that was more marble type but it had to be washed - cleaned before breakfast - 
a huge hall coming - passing several - oh I can't think how long. And then there was the staff's breakfast to be got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what other servants were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There was a - er - I was a kitchen maid, there was a cook and th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 
ere was - er - housemaid, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  and two nursemaids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did they all sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What the - well there's a nursery that was almost at the top of the house - top of the house was our bedrooms the next flight - er floor down was the nurseries, and then the n
ext floor down was the ladies bedrooms and then the drawing rooms and lower than that dining room on the level and then of course the basement where there was a pantry.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And where did you all eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The staff? Er - well of course the nurses had it with the children and the other staff had it in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there a sort of servants hall or anywhere the staff could sit when they weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, we had a servants hall - used to have our tea there, but our main meals - breakfast d
inner and supper we used to have in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And this household did the lady of the house supervise all the housework personally or pass orders through the senior staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, of course, naturally, she would - er - tell you what she, tell yo
u what she - er - expected of you and once you knew the routine, of course you done it - er - every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would she tell you personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. She'd tell you personally. I'd be in the house - I was a kitche
n maid first of all - then the cook would tell you. But then from there I went in the same place as a housemaid. Yes. So of course I got upstairs a bit - and then the lady would tell you what you had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you were a kitchen maid the cook told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Cook told you, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And when you were a housemaid the lady told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The lady, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel at ease with your other staff or members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Er - yes - we were very - er - happy staff together - 
but of course one had to you - you - er - were the lower servant - 'course the cook come first then the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 
 and housemaid and - er - you were sort of - er - do as you're told sort of thing.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel at ease with the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh we very seldom saw them. And then if we met them in the hall or anything we used to say good morning and they said good morning - they always called you by your surname then - yes - Tyler - so they'd say good morning, Tyler and you'd say good morn
ing, Madam or good morning Sir, whatever it might be and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel that any of them was interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes - these people were because - er - they were friends of my father's people - he worked for - the Jewish people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was their occupation the people that you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well - I don't know exactly what they - the occupation were he had - he had er - I suppose a job of some sort but what it was I couldn't tell you. He used to go out - I 
suppose to a office every morning and come home in time for - er - but the interesting part that I - rather took me - was of course being strict Jews - and we had to without bread for a week during the Pass-over, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you had to do the same as the rest of the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes. We could have it when we went out but we mustn't have - wasn't allowed to eat it when we come in - we had - er - quite nice m}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 atza}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , you know, the matza cakes and that - and all that sort of thing - quite nice. And duri
ng that time - before that time every tin and - biscuit tin had to be washed and cleaned and nothing must be brought in as regards bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the lady of this house give any moral guidance to the staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, of course, the cook was the head of 
the staff and if anything wanted - er - the lady used to come down every morning and give orders for - as regards - to give ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But apart from orders did she tell the staff how to behave - what's good and bad to do - not just work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well you were - you were trained sort of when you went into these jobs you knew exactly what you should do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She would advise you for instance on how you should conduct yourself going out with a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no. No. They never - that was - that was - er - our own affairs. But we had to be in at a certain time - we had to be in quite by 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}ten o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Yes, by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}ten o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were the staff allowed any time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well, you had the time in the afternoon when you'd finished 
your work - sort of between tea time and - and meal time - er - supper time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what time would supper time be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Supper time would be about - eight or half past when the people had finished their dinner - and then you had to go - there's more jo
bs to do - you had to go up and do - see to the beds and if there was hot water put up there you had to take hot water up if you wasn't - there was always ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When could the staff go out of the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - we were allowed out once - one afternoo
n a week and - er - half day on - er half day on every other Sunday. Yes. Half day - that meant you've got to finish your work and after lunch - that would be about two or three until about ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did your employer mind what you did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. It was nothing to do with them what you did outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you still had to be back by ten o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Always had to be back by ten, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In that household did you feel homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I didn't because it was more staff - er - yes - more staff a
nd the children - there was two - two or three or four children there so it was quite nice and being the kitchen maid I used to have to take up their meals to the - er - take it all upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you have enough companionship, you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes
, there was two of us - the housemaid and I share a room together - we were very friendly - we were friendly staff altogether quite - quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about that job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes - I didn't dis - I didn't like doing that flipping grate of a morning - I didn't like it but I had to do it and that was that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Anything you liked particularly about that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I just liked my work when I was doing it and - er - and one knew you had to do it an
d if you didn't do it - well - you'd get the sack if you didn't do it properly. So that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In that house how did the housework go - did they send the washing out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - yes - there was a Laundry - they sent the washing out - of course, the
 nurses done the children's things but all the other used to go out. Even our uniforms used to go out - our pink dresses and aprons used to go out - you were allowed a certain amount of money for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember who made or mended the family's clothes in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well that come under the housemaid - the housemaid had to do all the household linen and - er - the ladies things and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  done the gentleman's and the er - the sort of valeting and his sort of ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So you as a housemaid later on would have done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, oh yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the cooking was done by the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The cook - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I expect the lady was if there was any improvement wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In this household where did the adults eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well the lady and gentleman used to have their meals in the dining room and, of course, the children in the nursery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The children in the nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any exceptions to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - I think the children - being a Jewish family - I think the children came down every Friday night - 'cos their Sunday starts - sunset to sunset - from Saturday night to Sunday night, 
you see, and I think the children come down Friday, 'cos they were a very strict family and they used to even break bread and have wine and I think the children come - the older children - not the younger ones - came down - just for the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any adults with the children when they ate apart from the nanny and the nursemaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the adults eat at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well they had the - the parents had theirs in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what sort of cooking equipment there was in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh a huge big fire - an open grate, yes. A big open grate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you cooked on that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 A range was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, a range. Huge big thing - and it had to be polished every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Who had to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I did it. I was kitchen maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You had to polish it every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Blacklead - used to have - er - it was blacklead in a block to buy it and we used to put it in a small jar and put some water 
to it and then put all this on 'til it dried then polish it off with a - polish it off with a brush - filthy job. Not only that - there was all the ashes from the fire and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You had to clean all that out as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes. Had to be done before cook come down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The staff round about eight - so that meant I would have to be up about half past six. Quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You were up at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 6}}}half past six{\*\xmlclose} and had breakfast about eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about the people of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh probably they'd have it about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}half past eight{\*\xmlclose} to nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what members of the family were present at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh just mother and father - 'cos the children was upstairs in the nursery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what food was eaten at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh I think they ate very well there. They had - I couldn't tell you what they had - different things different days - but they ate very well there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what about you - did you eat well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, we had very good meals there - very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No - er - every day was different and more often than not if they - people were in for - er - evening meal - the staff had what's left over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How about Sunday, did they have anything special on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well no - I think they had a joint - a big joint of some sort or a bird of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they make anything like bread, jam or bottled fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I think - er - cook might have done some - er - jams at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Bottled fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never seen that done, but I think jam, jams and marmalade I think she used to make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about pickles and wine, beer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I never seen anything like that done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have a garden, did they grow their own fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, they had no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They bought fruit and vegetables for the household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, it was all bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Tinned or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well I suppose in what little tinned stuff there was would be helpful but there was always plenty of food going that could be bought in - er - see - so that's before the war you see so everything you could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And they didn't have a garden so they didn't keep hens or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember how many times a week they ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Um - 'course they didn't eat meat - when was it - not for - they never ate pork, of course, er - yes - meat most days I
 suppose, if I can remember rightly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the children, servants and parents have the same food or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The children used to have lighter foods, such as rice - milk puddings and steamed fish and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about the staff and the people in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - well no - they used to have - er - well of course the dining room used to have better food than we did - - oh yes, of course - and we had - it was very good food - all the same - nothing was wrong about that - but of course they 
used to have all theirs done with cream and all you know, nice things, but we used to get good wholesome food. Good roast joint and - er - and that and enough of it - we could always come again if - if we wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What was the basic difference between the food you ate and they ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh theirs was more elaborately done and richer food altogether of course, we had just good wholesome plain food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In 1912 you went to this house in Harley Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Harley Street, yes. Another Jewish family - I was there for five years - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What position did you have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I was housemaid - single-handed housemaid first of all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Single-handed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Single-handed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - that's - er - on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How many other servants were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There's four. Wait a minute - one, two, wait a minute - housemaid, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 
parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 , cook - between maid, housemaid, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 and ladymaid - five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did they sleep and eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - cooke - the - er - she was an elderly person and one of the big
 - she had fifteen children - Sulliman - that's a real Jewish name isn't it - but she was a very sweet old lady - got on very well with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she live by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - she lived there by herself but often the children come and stay there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And she had five servants just for herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - uh-huh. Yes. It was a good size house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there a servants hall in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the lady of the house supervise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel at ease in this house with the other staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. We were very happy. Er - one - the cook when I first went there wasn't a very pleasant person but - er - being she was head of the staff we had to sort of bide by it but we didn't sort of mix with her much sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she stay all the time you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No - she left - er - I think she went on - during the war - it was during the war see we were there - she left and done munition work. Then of course we had another cook in which was a much nicer person, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did all the staff get on with the lady of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In that household how did you address each other, in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, they used to call you by your surname - Tyler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She called you {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Tyler{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - and we used to have to call her Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what did the other staff call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er by - call me? By my Christian name, yes. And other names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the lady, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Sulliman - was she interested in you personally? Did she ever ask you anything about yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - she knew I come from a poor family and - er - I don't think she knew my father - like his job - like the other one did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she ever give you any sort of moral guidance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - er - the only thing was during the war - during the war we
 weren't - er - allowed men friends, but of course when they went away of course we found men friends you see and he used to come in once now and again and somebody opposite must have - er - told us and next year she said oh Tyler, she said, I heard last 
y
ear that you had men friends in while I was away so I said Madam, I said, excuse me, I said, but, I said, I've got several brothers who's in the army, I said, surely there allowed to come and see me once now and again. I got out of that. My brothers used 
to come of course but these - oh no. So I was - that was me all over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And in that house were you allowed any time to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - well we had our - er - short time in the afternoon - er - housemaid of course had to be dressed by
 - you know in a black dress and apron so that she could help wait at table as well - and - er - during the afternoon we used to be dressed by - what we called dressed - by tea time and then we just had that short time after - after tea 'til - the meal st
arted again. Or the beds got to be done or the water of the blinds to be - er - fires to be made up and coals to be taken up and that sort or thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She kept all the fires going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, yes, yes. The open fires and what do you call it grates as well, steel grates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And when could you go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Once a week. Yes, that's the usual run - er - once a week, no, one afternoon. And when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  I had to do - lay my table up for about six or seven and wash up the lunch things which probably 
she'd had people - her daughters in - then you'd lay up those - by the time I got out it was really somewhere round about four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And were you a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  in this house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Well I was housemaid first of all, yes, then I took on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 left and she asked if I'd like to take on the parlour work which I did do. Yes, I liked that better, it was much - a bit cleaner than - I had to do me own rooms - had to do the dining room and the library - then I used to clean
 all me own silver which was quite a lot - everything was silver in those days - silver dishes things like that. And - er - valet any gentleman that stayed there. That was parlourmaid's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you went out did she mind what you did or what time you got back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, well she used to mind what time you got back but we had to be back at ten that was - that was the average time - yes - but I used to rush home and see mum and then we'd go and meet a boy friend after that but used to have to rush back
 home again at ten, so we didn't get much time - and every other Sunday - every - only an afternoon and evening every other Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you feel homesick in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no, no, once you were out you know, it was fun mixing with the girls 
and we met different tradesmen that used to come. Jim, my husband, was one of them and we had real fun there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's where you met your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Used - er - I used to call him at the window and take some steak out of his basket - that was a
n order - an order that had to go to another lady, but of course coming }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 back with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 his cart we used - I used to knock at the window and say come in but he wouldn't come in so then when we were on - he used to say well you'd best have that now and he had to go back and get some more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about that job? Apart from the fact you met your husband there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, well I didn't think - we met him there but I didn't think much of - much to it then because I th
ought he was being friendly with my - with the - my - the other maid, you see, but no - I didn't - it was a very hard job because it was er - when I first went there as a housemaid all the floors were new parquet boards and they wasn't bought waxed at all
 and we - I had to get them all waxed up - that was a hard job - and we had to turn a room out before breakfast. That - turn out a room that probably means putting the curtains in bags and doing all the bits.....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Put the curtains in bags?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - 
used to turn the curtains back - for the dust to get on them while sweeping - and put them in bags and then all little bits of brass on the windows had to be brassed and the - er - probably brass fire-irons and - er - or - er - bits of brass ornaments and
 everything like that. There was a big writing desk in one of the rooms which was inlaid with brass - that had to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Every day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - and the fires had to be done which was - er - steel and the steel had to look like silver - us
ed to have to use a burnisher for that. You know what a burnisher is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. What's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 It's a big piece of leather about that square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 About four inches square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - but - er - with chains - very fine chain - and after you'd done this
 with er - what did you clean it with now - black stuff - um - wait a minute - well after you'd done it with this - put the black stuff on - used to polish it with this chain - used to rub the chain up it and backwards and forwards until it just shone. Em
ery paper, that's right, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 emery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 paper, yes. And that's before breakfast - before breakfast that is. Before ever you think of laying breakfast. Or probably if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  Sulliman - was an elderly lady - she used to have her breakfast in bed on a tray - but sometimes she come down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you snatch anything to eat before breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh we had a cup of tea - yes cup of tea, probably a biscuit but then we used to have to wait until breakfast time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How did the housework go in that house, was the washing sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, oh yes, and we were allowed a certain amount a week - sent our washing out - were allowed up to half-a-crown, and that meant, 'cos you had to be long white aprons - rotten big bows to the back - but that - we used to have to turn the
m round to make your bow - so it stuck up - and - your - dresses right down to the ground - and used to wear high heals at that, I mean to say, well you couldn't see your feet. That's why I got bad feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you were the housemaid first in that job did you mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - the ladies maid done the ladies clothes but I had to do the household - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about making clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - there was nothing made - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the cooking was done again by the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - the cook and the between maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And repairs to the house and improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well it - it was pretty well a new house - with - er - made into a new house when we first went there 'cos it was the - er - first time she took it on - I followed the family in - and that's when all the floors were new and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There wasn't any needed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Oh there wasn't any needed - but then 'course she used to have the house done up - you know - the inside done up sometimes - the staircase and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did the lady eat her meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the dining room. In the dining room, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Apart from breakfast on a tray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember the cooking equipment in the kitchen there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Kitchen range and a g
as stove they had there - and a gas stove - yes. Er - the kitchen range heated - heated the water from - for the baths upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when breakfast was eaten in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When? At what time? We'd have ours first at about eightish a
nd - er - if she had hers on a tray - round about nine - or if she was downstairs round about the same time. She had an operation while I was there, you know - at seventy - two - for gall stones - had it in the house. In the house - yes - a bedroom had to
 be got ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The surgeon came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. One of her sons was - er - a doctor but of course he didn't have anything to do with it, but he was there, but - oh yes, we had all the place to get ready and all that - windows to be done over and all tha
t for it. Yes, yes and she showed me the - well we saw the gall stones after it - they were put in - er - spirit - yes - they were like little round pieces of mud or - yes - dried mud it looked like - and she got six - had six you know taken out. Seventy-
two - yes - she had that operation. And she had fifteen children. That was almost the last year before I - I left her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And was she a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes. They're - er - I think business was ostrich feathers. Ostrich feathers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What importing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
I wouldn't know - but I know something to do with ostrich feathers. But he was dead before I went there - marvellous looking man he was too - she had a bronze bust of him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember what was eaten at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What for us? Oh
 yes, we either had bacon - Jewish family again - there - wasn't allowed pork in the house or anything like that - but we had - we could have bacon - er - downstairs - not upstairs - er - herrings one morning or kippers or haddock whatever it might be. We
 had quite good food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And what did the lady have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh all sorts of things - she used to have something like a scrambled egg, being that age you see she didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 want}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - and toast. When I used to have to call her in the morning I used to have to take 
her a silver jug of hot water and I was a bad one always for getting up in the morning and many a time I'd think to myself ooh heavens, I'd nip downstairs with me hat - cap and apron on over me nightdress. And she'd say to me '
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Tyler{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, what's the time?' I'd say '{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 7}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 Madam'. Probably it was quarter past. And she had a little clock - little watch - timekeeper - and it used to ting - ting the time out but she never said a word. Many a time I used to nip down there with me nightdress on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She didn't notice?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, no, so long as I got me cap and apron on I was all right - I - me pink frock of course - wasn't on but had a big apron and cap stuck on top of me head - oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And in that house did they make any of their own things, bread, jam ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - cakes and all that sort of thing and - er - yes jam sometimes when they were - but not - I don't think - pickles or anything like that - jams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Or bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Fruit and vegetables - did they bottle them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, it's every small house, original house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember how many times a week they ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well of course they was - they used to go in for all these - er - posh things - plovers 
eggs and quails if they had dinner parties and all that sort of thing, used to have very good meals - about seven or eight courses, more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Even in this house with only one lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well if she was on her own she used to have about two o
r three - little soup of some sort and one little fish and little meat or something and - sweet of some sort. But - er - as I say it was a big family - there was always someone coming up from the country coming in - there was very seldom a day without som
ebody staying there - that's what made it hard, you see, several people - the rooms were all full - the bathrooms had to be used that sort of thing and then of course they'd invite people for dinner and that so of course more often than not .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the staff eat the same food as the lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, we didn't have anything that glamorous but we had good - very good food yes, yes very good food, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did the staff eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the - er - servants hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In 1917 you went to Sloane Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 This job you left at about the end of 1918 - you were there....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Before 1918 - er - wait a minute - wait a minute - 1918 I was at what do you call its before 1918 because the war was finished and I was in another job after that. E
r - that'd be about eighteen months and then she offered me a job to go to Frinton - a friend of hers - an American lady and - er - that - that job was similar to one I had before - I was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 
parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - there was three of us - three - four - one - two - four of us there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 This was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Sloane Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Sloane Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - yes. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 Sidney Clarke. But I left eighteen months - I thought I'd like to go - after I was there five years I thought to myself I wouldn't stop in another place - I'd go and - gain mo
re - each job you went to you gained more - different ways what different people had you see and then I thought I'd gain more experience - well I think they gave up the house after a time and she asked me if I would - er - she wanted to recommend me to a 
friend of hers at - er - in - going to Frinton - got a house at Frinton, so it was a temporary job because her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 was ill - so I said yes I'd do it and I was there eight months altogether. But - er - we went all over the place - we had - er - the p
lace at Frinton, we stopped there fore - er - there was only three of us there then - she was living with her brother-in-law because the wife was in France with an invalid son - so she sort of kept house for him and they were both very heavy drinkers - an
d
 - er - then we went to Frinton because the troops were stationed there - er - then we went to Holt in Norfolk and - er - for a time and then the troops were - er - moved on again and then we went to Cromer. And during the time she had a flat in Whitehall
 
Court and either - myself or the cook used to go up with her for a couple of days and we - you know, make a change and she had - and then when they got to Cromer they used to entertain a lot - er - officers and that - we used to dancing with different reg
i
ments at the station there - I never missed one and - er - and 'course you know when you got bad feet - and - er - they were such big drinkers that - er - when they had dinner after their coffee they always had it in a port wine glass and they used to hav
e
 sometimes two or three of those. I used to make five shillings a week on bottles 'cos in those days bottles were always sold for a penny each, you know, see, and when the man come to collect them they were what they called the parlourmaid's perks they we
re.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you get on well with ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
I got on well - yes with her - but I didn't get on well with him because he thought I was one of the troops. He used to shout along the passage 'Dowd' I said 'did you call me' and then the boys used to come in
 for orders every day and there was always a drink for them - but - er - she was a drug addict - I didn't know that 'til afterwards. And the last I - after I left - I saw in the paper that she'd shot herself - killed herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And had the war finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - the war - the war finished in 1918 while I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 While you were working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right. Because we had - er - a sort of a - with the troops - sort of a - what can you call it now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Celebration?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not exactly c
elebration - well - yes - I suppose it would be a celebration - we had a few hymns and that sort of thing on the big green with - so many of the soldiers there. His regiment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the war actually finished while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Finished while I w
as there - yes - 1918 - and that finished in the - November was it - yes - in November as my sister was killed in the - er - month before - in October.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you get on with the other staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Staff? Yes, oh yes, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There were two others were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, two others, yes. Cook and - er - between maid, we used to call 'em - she used to do a little bit upstairs and little bit downstairs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did this particular lady - was it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3173772\charrsid10431346 Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - she was a Miss Hugmeyer? Yes. She was an American lady.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did she mind when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well yes, we were allowed to go out any afternoon so long as ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You could go out any afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, if - if we wanted to - but of course as I say the war was on and the even
ings got dark in the wintertime so we didn't want to go out very far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have any official time off like in the other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - we - er - it wasn't - exactly like one Sunday like beforehand but we - if there's no people there we went out,
 you see, and then we had out free time with - we used to go dancing quite a lot because - er - different troops that were stationed down there - them being the officers, you know, used to ask them back again or - and the staff as well. But only two of us
 used to go so I ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel homesick in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, once I left home and was in service it - it was just that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And was there anything you particularly liked or disliked in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no, I didn't dislike it but - er - I
 found out afterwards that - er - she was a drug addict and during that time which I didn't realize the doctor used to come and inject her then, which I didn't find out until afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 It didn't bother you at the time because you didn't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, I didn't know at the time - it didn't bother me afterwards - I thought well that's what she wants to do that's - that's her life - didn't interfere with us. But the only thing I didn't like was - which I didn't like there - er - I went into the bathro
om one day and apparently she was injecting the cook too. And I didn't realize that 'til - er - she come into me she said 'oh - er - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Tyler{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - don't - er - don't go into Grace's room she's not very well'. Well I thought she wasn't very well but afterwards I found out that's what she had done to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she become an addict - the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well now and again, I suppose she must have done. Then I found out afterwards that - well afterwards I found out she was a drug addict and - er - in fact I saw it in 
the paper - then of course everything come back to me. I don't - don't misjudge anybody - I never used to misjudge her - but admitted she used to go to bed quite a lot and have all the drugs on the bed and the doctor used to come quite often and - er - he
 used to say Miss Hugmeyer's not very well. Well, I thought Miss Hugmeyer wasn't very well and that was that - but that's - er - what it was. Then to my surprise I saw in the paper soon after that she'd shot herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And he was very sort of authoritarian man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes - well big - er - he was a Scotch - he belong to the Highlanders - Sutherland Highlanders - he was shortish but - and the most ugliest man I've ever seen. But not at heart when he wasn't with the troops - and course when anyone was
 there he'd just yell at me as if I was one of the soldiers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What would you say to him when he did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - I used to look at him and said - er - 'course I couldn't be too rude you see because - er - I had learnt me manners - and I - I used to
 look at him and I said 'are you speaking to me Sir'. 'Yes' he says, and off we go. So that was that. I used - er - I weren't scared of his ways so it did not good to shout at me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In this last household how did the housework go there, did you send the washing out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I did all the parlourwork - yes - and valet - no - a man used to come in - er - majors valet used to come in and see to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about the washing in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - washing was sent out the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And mending families clothes - making things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes, well I used to do - no - his - and well if there was anything done the cook used to do them 'cos she was - er - more a friend of the family as far as I could gather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There were no children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No - she was a miss you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where did they eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Cooking equipment - do you remember what was in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - it was only a small cottage in the country and I think there was a small I think a very small stove -
 with a gas stove I think, a gas stove was usually that about - er - with something else, you see, but I think there was a small stove there. It was only a small cottage actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember when breakfast was eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, she always had he
r breakfast in bed - but very often - more often than not didn't want breakfast - just had tea - I used to take her tea in in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When she woke up - when she rang the bell. More often than not it was ab
out sometimes ten or eleven in the mornings later than that sometimes. Then she'd say to me 'Tyler, I want some magazines - take my bike' and away Tyler used to go on the bike - and go all round - meet some boyfriends - er - and go and get all the magazin
es you could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And when did you eat your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh in the kitchen. Yes, round about eight - nine. That's usually the time we start breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Presumably you didn't do all this making bread, jam and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I think Grace used to do quite a lot of - er - jams and marmalades - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Pickling fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so - no I never saw anything done, but I know mostly being Scotch she used to do those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have a garden at the cottage there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There was a garden but there was nothing - nothing in it much because being wintertime you see....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Didn't keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Only - well - three dogs. Yes. They're domestic - that's right - and one dog was - er - not a
 - an English Labrador - a shooting dog and when they used to go out shooting grouse they never used to put - they had their soldiers clothes on and that dog used to know in a minute - he'd crawl underneath the cupboard and stop there until he was told to
 
come out. He was a lovely dog - I used to play with him sometimes with a slipper. And I used to say to him stop, sit - and he'd sit down there and directly I said all right come on find it - no matter where I put it he'd find it. That was all done during 
your work time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember how often meat was eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Meat? Ooh we had plenty of meat - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 although}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  there was very little meat going - being in the army we got crowds of meat. Somebody's rations I suppose we had but it wasn't ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So going back to the house that you lived in and worked in in 1908 which was the one where you first went after you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes. With the two old ladies. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember anything that they did on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I can't, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there any musical instruments, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There? No there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Never heard - not even hum. I'm always humming even - even now. No, no, they were very sort of serious - it was mother and da
ughter - very serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - there was plenty of books around - but what sort they were I couldn't tell you. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not in that - no, no, not in that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There were just the two old ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember did the two old ladies think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - I'm trying to think - I don't think I went in there Sunday. No, I can't remember going in there Sunday - so I wouldn't know - no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they go to church or to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well the church was right opposite the house but how often I wouldn't know. Because I didn't - yes - I know they went because I - as I didn't go in on Sunday I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you attend the same church as they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Three times a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you sit in the same place as they did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I never knew - I never knew where they sat - but us as from the school you see had a certain place to sit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 After you left school, did you go to church with them of a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was grace said at meals in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They had - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I - I suppose they did - but I don't know - was too young to know what they got up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they go out on their own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The younger person - but the other one was a very old lady - she couldn't go very far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But the daughter did go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you know where she went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I think she had some friends down at Weybridge somewhere and sometimes she'd go out for the day to these friends at Weybridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she have any other interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not that I know of, no. I suppose they did but - er - all as I was interested in was getting home to see mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 There wasn't a man in the house was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And they didn't have any occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They just had a little - I suppose they had a little money and - er - just bide them and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - I didn't see a great - I think one or two used to pop in now and again but not many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they come to eat or ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. I didn't - they might have
 come probably when I was - I was - home every evening - let off you know for the evening - they might have come when I was out but - er - I wouldn't know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But not during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No, very seldom. They seemed to be a very retiring couple of people, ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't remember any particular people who came to the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Do you think that these two ladies were content with their station in life or do you think they would have liked to have been in a higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, they seemed quite satisfied with life in general so I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 presume}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  they were satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Had you known people like them before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well my - all my sisters - four - three other sisters went to the same place before I got there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So they'd talked to you about what they were like, had they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But had you actually ever personally ever met anyone like them before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No, I hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well I knew I had to go and w
ork there and I knew had - I had to be obedient and do as I was told and - er - and I did what I was told. But the old lady was a very old lady - she got very fractions at times but - er - they used to upset me a bit and then I used to go home - run away 
-
 and go and tell mum I wouldn't come back any more. But the old lady used to come - it's walking distance from my home - you see - from the church to Alexander Street, and presently the old lady would be coming along - pottering along with her stick and c
alling up the stairs to mother and saying that I'd run away and of course I had to go back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think of their way of living in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Their way of living? Er - well - I - er - I was young and didn't know any different - didn't k
now of any other way of living - I had to go out to work - we didn't go very far so I didn't know any different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did their manners and general behaviour seem different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh - yes - they were quite nice people - oh yes, they was - er - quite nice 
to me, you see, in their way, the daughter was very nice - I got on with her very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can we go back and do the same questions for the next house you lived in? That was the one where you were ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Kitchen maid - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So the secon
d family you were in from 1909 til 1911 as a kitchen maid. Can you remember anything the family did together on Christmas Day there? Were you there on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, I suppose I was there Christmas 'cos I was there two years - er - that was - it
 was a Jewish family - no I think we had - we had the usual sort of parties - sort of - er - with the children upstairs - the children used to come down to the - the dining room with their parents and - er - they used to have little sort of presents and t
hat sort of thing and - er - I think the staff down below just give one and other presents at Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there any musical instrument in the home in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't remember anyone playing anything there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Anyone in the family who sang?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever make music together as a family, presumably not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - you and the other people in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well of course that was a different thing altogether - the 
family kept themselves to their own quarters and we had to keep to our quarters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about downstairs in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well we used to get a little communal together - probably a sing-song if we didn't make too much noise - but we were all ha
ppy, you know, four or five of us together all quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the parents play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I don't think they saw a great deal of the children because they had two nannies you see and - er - and in those times the childre
n were just given to the nannies and the mothers used to see them - go up and say good night to them and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the nannie play games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, they would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you actually see them ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no -
 I never seen them but - er - I presume, naturally children want entertaining don't they - so I presume nannies - they used to go out mornings and afternoons with the prams - used to take them out you see so ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And were there any books in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh I expect so but I can't - one doesn't remember - I was - just - plenty of childrens books - used to be in their nursery there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But adults books - did they have lots of bookshelves and library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well there was always a room called a library so - that'd be all classical books I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember the mother or father reading aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - only at prayer time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember a funeral in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Presumably as the children were given over to a nanny you never took them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh no, no. Nannie's responsibility, yes. All I had to do was take the food up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ever go out with the Master and the Mistress on a weekend or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh goodness no - it wasn't done. Staff mixing with the Missus - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the master and mistress think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I think they were very strict - er - Jewish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So it would have been Saturday for them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes Saturday - Friday night 'til sunset 'til Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And they were strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes very strict Jews - that's why we had to go without bread for a week. Very strict Jews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did they go to the synagogue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't think they went in the week time but they always went Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Both of them together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the children go to the synagogue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I suppose they did when they were older because they were only young when I was there - small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But not as children - they didn't go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not that I know of - no. I suppose when they're old enough to understand then probably they would go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did any of you who were working there go to the same church as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, 'cos we never went to a synagogue - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
What upstairs? Er - well we weren't there - er - to know if grace was said. Well prayers - they used to have prayers on a Friday night - their Sunday. Friday night - that was special - and used to hav
e bread - break bread and have wine - special wine for - for - sunset.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't participate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they take an interest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 in politics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose they did, but what they did I - I wouldn't know. What they did never - never in
terested us - we had to wait on them and - er - that was that. What they done apart from that of course we wouldn't know. That's right. Probably they were interested in something very special but - er - that's the sort of thing - the parlour maid would kn
ow more about that than the kitchen maid, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you know if the master took part in any sport, went to the races, played cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. He wasn't that type of gentleman - he was very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did he go to a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Might have done - I wouldn't know that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the Mistress go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Only used to go at home - used to go out to tea - they used to be called at homes - they - different peoples houses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she have any other interest outside the home? Any work for charities or committees or anything like that, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Probably they did but - er - I don't remember - downstairs you see you don't know anything what happens upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember them ever going out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What th
em going out together? Er - oh yes they used to go out for dinner and all that sort of thing and - and they'd have some commitments during the day, but I wouldn't know what - what they were doing - and I wouldn't even - I wouldn't even know if they went o
ut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I can't remember - I can't recall what his business was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was he ever away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And if he was - for long or for short periods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't think he ever - I can't remember him ever going awa
y. They used to go away with the children for holidays in the summertime but that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, people used to pop in for luncheons and dinners and they used to go out to different people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they ever come to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - no, not - not there, not that I can remember - if they did I wouldn't know - 'cos I was the kitchen maid, you see. You don't know anything what happens upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember, was the lady of the house the same class would you say as the gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes. They were just the same - M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 catt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10113835\charrsid10431346 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
? was the name - that's a real Jewish name isn't it? And they were very nice people, I got on well - very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember the behaviour of any of the guests towards the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, as I say again I was I was downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think that this particular lady and gentleman you worked for were content with their station in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I presume so, as I say again, you don't - er - don't get involved in their - affairs. In their way of living really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well, as I say again, I was paid to - to do the work for them and that was all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have any private thoughts about them though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, but I knew t
hey were a station above me and - er - that they paid me wages for what I done and - er - and - er - I had to do what was expected of me and that was that. That's been all along and - er - in my life anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did their manners and general way they behaved seem different from people you'd associated with before?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, they was very polite - they didn't used to speak to you a great deal but if they met you, which was very seldom, they always used to say good morning - pass the time of the day and you used to say good morning back and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So in about 1911 you went to Harley Street and you were there for ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Five years - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember anything the family did together on Christmas Day in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well she was a
nother elderly - well this was another elderly lady and she had a big - tell you a big family - fifteen and there was always somebody staying there so of course there would be - but she lived there alone - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
They had a piano there and sometimes she would play the piano but very seldom. And - er - well she would play - she wouldn't play - it was a sort of pianola. Yes. And she used to put it on and it used to sound lovely. When different people come there pr
obably they would play it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember her children or any other members of the family singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In that household did you make any music together, downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, no, because it was a rather small house and sound would - er - would carry - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Were there lots of books or newspapers, magazines in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Quite a few books and things - magazines - papers that - you know, every day papers used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember a funeral in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What from the house? No, no, not from the house, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did this lady think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She's Jewish again so Sunday didn't - er - didn't matter again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was she a strict Jew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, but she did
n't go out - she was seventy - I told you she had an operation at seventy-two - and I'm seventy-six for that matter - but - er - they used to go out different times but - er - not - she didn't used to go out a great deal. If she did go out she went out in
 a carriage, and just for a drive round somewhere or to visit people or friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she go to the synagogue herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't - I presume so - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But you don't remember exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't - I suppose if they went out to a church naturally it would be a synagogue wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What about if her children came?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no. No grace was said, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Presume so, but as I say I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You said she went out on her own for a drive in a carriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 To see friends or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you know if she had any other interests outside the house? Any charities or committees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, I should imagine so b
ecause they seemed to be - er - not exactly rich family but - er - a family well - er - what can I say - how can I say now - well - er - family well together - united family like - that's what I'm trying to find and - er - they would be going out parties 
and one of them was - er - a big - had an awful lot of money in \{ILLEGIBLE\} - remember \{ILLEGIBLE\} do you - that was a great big - that was a big ... one of the sons }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - er - one of the daughters }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How long had she been a widow when you went their?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh she had been a widow I think quite a number of years before I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't know what he did before he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I know it was in the ostrich feather - er - company that they were in. I presume it was his business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she have many friends call to see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Apart from her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Yes. There was always friends coming in to - er - usually at homes - used to have - er - tea fights as we used to call 'em - but they called them at homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she ever have friends come to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh er - majority of them were her children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Apart from that did she have friends come to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not to stay. I don't think, no. The children were mostly in the country you know, and they come 
up for the - two or three days and stay - always stayed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember her ever treating the friends that came to see her in different ways or...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No she was always a very placid sort of lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember of the guests in this house - how they behaved towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well there was - just the same - you were the servant and they were the - the heads of the family and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think she was happy with her position in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I think so, yes, quite happy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And the children around her I suppose too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Had you known anybody like her - was she similar to the Jewish family you had worked for before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I suppose - she was similar because being Jewish you see you got different - er - they got 
different ways sort of to Christian people have got. But they never made it - er - uncomfortable for us because they were Jewish, no, we were quite happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 After you came away from Harley Street you went to Sloane Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Square, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And that was in about 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - it was - because in 1918 - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh about eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember anything in this family they did together on Christmas Day? This was the lady who was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  to the gentleman in the Army wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Can you remember a Christmas day in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, well they had two children - there was always a party for the children. I do remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - w
ell there used to be - er - she was a German lady and - er - there used to be some - er - people on the stage that used to be very good - well-known singers - I can't remember the names of them now - if I could remember them I think they would be interest
ing for your - er - gentleman - er - professor - and I just can't think of the name of them but they often used to come there and sing and the mother used to play the piano for them and they were well-known people in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And this was the lady who employed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right - yes. I tell you one person she had there - Constance Collier. Yes - well that was in those days and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And she came there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 She used to come there quite a lot - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So they made quite a lot of music together when people came down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they play with their children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well, they had a nurse - er - nursery governess and - er - they were people who don't play with their children a great deal - they go and see them but - er - I wouldn't see them play with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But the nanny did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember, were there books in this house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, there was plenty of books. Lot of German books - because they were Ger - originally German people. And - Mattesdorf was
 the name. Mattesdorf yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember either of them reading a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh well they often used to - read - go in and take their tea they'd be reading either a book of some sort or papers or what it might be.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So they read quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they read aloud to each other at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 To the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The children very seldom came down, you see, they were - the nursery people kept up with them at the top of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there a funeral in this family that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have any strong religious ideas about Sunday - did they think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, well it was during the war, you see, h
e had to - he was on duty quite a lot. He was on the - er - food - er - commission - getting food abroad to the soldiers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The way you described them to me earlier they sound rather free and easy people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh they were - very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They weren't very proper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, oh no - they were very - quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they go to church or chapel, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose they might have gone to church - I never - I never see them go of a Sunday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did the children go to church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They were too young you see while I was there - they wouldn't go then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In fact she had another young baby when I was there in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So she had three altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - but I think the children had to - would say it in the nursery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 So the nanny would say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, I suppose - that's a bit difficult to say - if she was German and
 he was English - he was an English gentleman - I suppose they had something or other in common or had their own ideas of - er - but I never knew what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't see how - he was in the Army and he used to come home probably at the weekends or ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You don't remember him going to the races or playing cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did he go to a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 He might have done, yes, but I wouldn't know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did this lady go out much on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes, she was always out - visiting friends and going out for lunch - having people for lunch and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did she have any other interest outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Not that I'm aware of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she work for any charities or sit for any committees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No - I think a lot of people done quite a lot of getting things together for the soldiers and - er - knitting and sending things for the soldiers and I think she had quite a bit - was quite a bit involved in - er - it - er - but not a great de
al I don't think. I think everybody sort of put themselves out during the war - even the people you worked for and the staff as well. Food - 'course food was very meager then because we were on rations and had ration books. Two ounces of margarine a week.
 
Yes we did - about one egg a week. Very - very little - about two ounces of cheese I think. Could hardly make it go round but they used to manage somehow - I know one - one day we had to have just - just vegetables alone, beans and butter beans and all th
at sort of thing. No meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 This was during the 1914-18 war was it while you were with this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
That's right - well - yes - with the Jewish people beforehand the war had only just started you see, well as it went on years and years of course t
hings got much shorter. Vegetables and everything like that, you see, then 'til the ration books come out then of course we had to be rationed, we had no more than that. So much meat every week - very little - and then we were - being in service - used to
 pool the books you see, when you'd get a fair - well not a fair piece - a small piece at that but you - so much bacon - so many rashers of bacon - very rare we eat that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember them going out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh when they'd finished work - to 
dinner parties and that sort of thing when there was the opportunity of course - he was mostly on duty of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And he was a Major in the Army did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - that was after that was a Major - now what was he - I think he was a - I thin
k he was a captain. Captain Clarke or Lieutenant - no Lieutenant Clarke. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was he away from home much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - no - he was stationed I think mostly at the dock - down the docks, you know, he was something to do with the food, you see, was - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But would he stay away nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, often he was - he'd - go away probably week ends or probably if he was on duty that weekend he'd come home when he could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What influence do you think this had on the way the household was run?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh - wasn't run any differently - except he wasn't there - but - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You say he used to shout at you - did you like it when he wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh not that one - no - that was - the job after that, that was when - the Major.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - quite a lot - I'm still trying to think of that big singer that used to come in. Directly you're gone I'll think of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, they used to come there quite a lot for dinner parties and that. An
d when they had this singing soiree as they - er - used to call it, 'course we used to see them. I was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 parlourmaid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
 there, you see, so of course the tea had to go up and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What kind of people were they, these friends and people who called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, quite - quite nice - always very - amiable - used to say good evening or good morning and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Similar sort of people to the people before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh, yes, yes, exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What sort of class would you say they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Wel
l they were just a - just a better class - I mean to say - Constance Collier she was just a - er - wonderful actress in those days and - er - they mixed with those sort of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was the lady in this house the same sort of class as the gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - I should say so - yes - quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember - did they treat some of their friends differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - they always seemed to be pleased to see them - no - they were pleased to see them and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember any of the ways these guests would behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Well all I used to do was let them in the front door, you see, and announce their names and they'd go into the drawing room, you see, and then when tea-time come I used to take their tea in and that's all I used to see of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you think they were happy with their position in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They seemed to be - er - they always seemed to be chatty and laughing together sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 They weren't ambitious particularly - socially ambitious - would have like to have been a higher class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Might have done but - as I said - one doesn't - those sort of things I'd say you'd get from their friends sort of thing - we wasn't to know - we weren't supposed to know what they - er - what they - above st
airs do. But you were put quietly down - not that it worried me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Had you known many people like them before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. I mean to say - the other people were Jewish you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 What did you think of them generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I got on with them very well. Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did their manners - general behaviour seem different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
He was a very nice gentleman - very nice - well so was she - she was very nice but I suppose at the back of my mind - I know she was German and that sort of - little - er -
 she was quite - sweet person - but - er - under the circumstances then I suppose it was just that one little feeling that I liked him better than I did her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 In your next job it was a brother-in-law and a sister-in-law living together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 This is the last job you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Before I went to - er - no - I - before I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1602578 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  I went to Bridgemans - I was there a short .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But the war finished while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 While I was at this place - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Do you remember Christmas Day - did Christmas Day happen while you were with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well no it didn't - I wasn't there at Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Any musical instruments in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no. No because we went from different places, you see, we traveled sort of with the troops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did either of them sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - but they used to shout. And you know - he was the ugliest man I ever met. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have lots of books in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - I don't remember seeing it - oh she used to like all the - er - magazines - er - magazines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You used to go out on the bicycle to get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - that's right - yes - when she was queer used to send me out on a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Was there a funeral in this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well the war was still on so everything had - to be - was every day, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they go to church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - I never seen them went - unless of course the Major went with the troops you see, the church service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. But we - but we had a cook called Grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - I don't think she took an interest in politics - in fact I think she took interest in drugs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did he take part in sport or go to the races, play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er no - he was very fond of shooting. Shooting - yes. And they used to take the dog -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 The labrador dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did she go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - no - very seldom. No - very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - I don't think she did - she just lived for her brother-in-law and looked after him and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they go out together at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - 'cos the war was on, you see, and - er - there wasn't much to go - we used to go to the dances - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2033373\charrsid10431346 troops}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346  - er - regiments was stationed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And you would go with them would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - and - er - I would go - yes - I would be their first to go there. And they used to invite 
the - the staff of them and that, you see, the Colonel and that used to come for dinner party of a night time and - 'course it was always previously arranged with some of the soldiers that used to come there that we would go - at least I and another of th
e staff would go and time we finished there would be about ten o'clock so of course we didn't get to bed - dance in time - but they'd always go - they'd open the dance and be there when you got there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And he was a major wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And was he away much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well no - he was in - that was the idea of it - he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - he was er - he was in the Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders and he ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 But was he away from home much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - because where the troops went she follow
ed him, you see, we'd - er - the troops were stationed in Frinton-on-Sea first of all and then they moved to - er - Cromer - that's where - where we were - but she had a flat in Whitehall Court and we used to go backwards and forwards with her there and s
top for two or three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did it make much difference when he was away with his station?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Er - well - we was always - we were all there, you see, we took er - a cottage or something at - the - each place he went to, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they have many friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - no - I don't think they did. Because, as I say, all their time was - er - was occupied with - with the Army and he used to go down to the head office - you know - the - er - head quarters - each day and - er - they used to be asked 
out here at - the Colonel as I say, used to come and they used to be asked back to their place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And do you think they were content with their position in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I - I suppose so - I mean to say, it - er - she never seemed to be content with 
things as they were - as life in generally though, 'cos as I say, I found eventually that she was drug taking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Had you know anybody like them before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. No, I hadn't. Oh she was - she was a very sweet person apart from that when I first went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 When you were actually working there, forgetting what happened afterwards, what did you think of them - their way of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, as I say, I was paid to do a job and I done it again and you find different types of people each - as years g
o on you find different types of people - they were a - er - an ordinary couple - er - they used to have their meals together and - er - drink an awful lot - awful lot, both of them, as I say, when they had coffee and kimmel with it and - that was - used 
t
o be - you know what that is - kummel - lovely isn't it - and so they had it just in a - instead of just a small glass they used to have a port glass and they used to have that about - filled up twice - and no matter who would come there - if the soldiers
 come there for orders or anything like that there was always a drink for them - plenty of stuff going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did they seem very different to you from people you'd worked for before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well they were a different type of people. She was American you see a
nd he was - er - he was Scottish actually - Adair - Campbell - that's what his name was - that's pretty well Scotch, isn't it. Until he used to shout and then - and he didn't frighten me though, but still - he used to shout as if I was one of the - one of
 the soldiers but that didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation if you'd had a choice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well we had - I had no time to think about it, I mean to say, we was in service and that was all there was. Er - well during the wa
r I did train to - er - after I left this Major's - I tried to go on the telephone - and I was on the telephone service - 'cos they were asking for people then and I just failed in some spellings so of course that's how - so I've gone back to service. Yes
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you belong to any Trade Union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Me? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well I suppose the same interest only they - they know they paid you for - er - working and - er - that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 I don't think so - no. I - as I say, that sort of thing wouldn't interest me - I was just interested in - in what I was doing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, I still lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 You didn't live at home after school, did you? You went on straight into service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Service - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
No, no. I think it made us more - closer to them because - er - as we hadn't seen them that much I used to rush home every five minutes I got. And that that was only two or three hours of a - once a week and every other Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did it change your attitude to your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well, the only thing - we only had half a day every other Sundays - so of course home I us
ed to chase, you see, and see mother. Spent it at home - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No. Not a bit interested in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way - not that you had very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Well - around the age of getting boy-friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And how old was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 How old? Oh I suppose I started at about seventeen - eighteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you go out in the evenings - your evening off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh - only - yes, I used to go home first to tea and then if I got a boy friend to meet I used to go out and meet the boyfriend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 
Er - mostly walks because - er - those days the - er - the Grenadier Guards was - er - favourite. I can - and they hadn't got a bean to - to spend on anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you go out with Grenadier Guards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Oh yes, yes, lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 And did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No, I - mostly used to meet my sisters and then we used to probably go to a dance or something if we had a chance to
 go - meet some other friends there - mostly Lifeguards then - because we were - that the nearest dance hall to use was - er - near the - er - Knightsbridge barracks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 No - we - we always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1854332 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Mostly your sisters wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10246374 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9056586\charrsid10431346 Yes - my sister - before she died, you see.
\par }}